WEBVTT

1
00:01:17.369 --> 00:01:19.538
Best place we went to
since we've been here.

2
00:01:19.621 --> 00:01:20.914
Definitely. man.

3
00:01:20.998 --> 00:01:22.708
- Way to go. buddy.
- Brother.

4
00:01:22.791 --> 00:01:26.086
- You guys coming back to my place?
- All right. Let's go.

5
00:01:29.590 --> 00:01:30.716
Hey!

6
00:01:31.592 --> 00:01:34.928
Shame. shame.
Closing down the beer garden.

7
00:01:35.429 --> 00:01:38.640
Hundred-metre dash
powered by knackwurst and lager.

8
00:01:39.933 --> 00:01:41.852
Where are you guys from?

9
00:01:43.270 --> 00:01:44.938
What's your event?

10
00:01:46.857 --> 00:01:48.859
They don't speak English. man.

11
00:01:50.611 --> 00:01:53.864
- Let's help them over.
- Come on. Up?

12
00:01:54.281 --> 00:01:55.490
Here you go.

13
00:01:56.617 --> 00:01:58.910
Let's go. I got you. Come on.

14
00:02:00.912 --> 00:02:03.707
Up. Yeah. All right?

15
00:02:08.920 --> 00:02:11.089
- You guys take care.
- See you.

16
00:02:13.050 --> 00:02:14.885
- Take it easy.
- See you.

17
00:02:14.968 --> 00:02:16.887
You're taking the grade tomorrow.

18
00:02:16.970 --> 00:02:18.639
Watch yourself. man.

19
00:03:54.651 --> 00:03:55.986
I'm Jim McKay speaking to you live

20
00:03:56.111 --> 00:03:58.572
at this moment. from ABC headquarters

21
00:03:58.655 --> 00:04:01.867
just outside the Olympic village
in Munich. West Germany.

22
00:04:01.950 --> 00:04:04.911
The peace of what have
been called the "serene Olympics”

23
00:04:04.995 --> 00:04:08.498
was shattered just before dawn
this morning. about 5:00.

24
00:04:09.541 --> 00:04:12.169
There is great uncertainty
about how many Israelis

25
00:04:12.294 --> 00:04:14.504
are being held hostage in the apartment.

26
00:04:14.671 --> 00:04:17.466
It now appears that Black September
has tossed a piece of paper

27
00:04:17.549 --> 00:04:19.885
out the window. A list of demands.

28
00:04:19.968 --> 00:04:22.679
They want what they call
"the Israeli war machine"

29
00:04:22.763 --> 00:04:26.349
to release 200 Arabs. which it
insists are political prisoners

30
00:04:26.433 --> 00:04:28.685
or the hostages will be killed.

31
00:04:29.102 --> 00:04:31.104
The terrorist communiqué ends
with an appeal

32
00:04:31.188 --> 00:04:34.274
for revolutionaries of the world to unite.

33
00:04:34.941 --> 00:04:38.403
This is building number 31.
At this moment.

34
00:04:39.196 --> 00:04:42.324
eight or nine terrified
living human beings

35
00:04:42.407 --> 00:04:44.284
are being held prisoner.

36
00:04:44.367 --> 00:04:47.871
The demands have been many...
There's someone right now.

37
00:04:48.205 --> 00:04:50.499
This certainly has to be
one of the guerrillas.

38
00:04:50.582 --> 00:04:53.877
A man with a stocking mask
on his face. Weird.

39
00:04:54.211 --> 00:04:57.005
What's going on inside that head
and that mind?

40
00:04:57.088 --> 00:04:58.965
Just a short while ago. there was

41
00:04:59.049 --> 00:05:01.968
another in this long series
of negotiations.

42
00:05:02.719 --> 00:05:06.556
The spokesman for the group
came out. spoke. went back.

43
00:05:06.640 --> 00:05:10.352
It seems to be a process
of speak and consultation.

44
00:05:10.435 --> 00:05:13.271
Does it mean it's all right?
Or does it mean it's all over?

45
00:05:13.396 --> 00:05:14.856
Come and get us.

46
00:05:14.940 --> 00:05:17.567
As Peter Jennings indicated.
the German army.

47
00:05:17.651 --> 00:05:21.112
because of very complicated laws.

48
00:05:21.279 --> 00:05:23.031
would not be allowed to participate.

49
00:05:23.114 --> 00:05:26.284
And there you see an athlete
holding a canvas bag

50
00:05:26.409 --> 00:05:28.411
in which is obviously a machine gun.

51
00:05:28.495 --> 00:05:30.288
Peter Jennings. once again. is stationed

52
00:05:30.413 --> 00:05:32.666
inside the Olympic village.
With the naked eye. Peter.

53
00:05:32.749 --> 00:05:34.125
what do you see now?

54
00:05:34.251 --> 00:05:37.087
Jim. there are now a great many.

55
00:05:37.170 --> 00:05:40.715
maybe a dozen already.
of those security men

56
00:05:40.799 --> 00:05:43.009
in athletic uniforms.

57
00:05:45.762 --> 00:05:50.100
We warned them.
we said what would happen if there's any attempt.

58
00:05:50.767 --> 00:05:54.271
so I think. we have to do it.
It's just a show.

59
00:05:54.437 --> 00:05:58.817
it's just a display to show the world
they know how to think and be organised.

60
00:05:58.942 --> 00:06:02.487
Go talk to them. go tell them to get back
or something bad will happen.

61
00:06:03.446 --> 00:06:04.489
Stop!

62
00:06:05.532 --> 00:06:07.993
It now appears that the siege
of the apartment building

63
00:06:08.118 --> 00:06:10.161
where the hostages are being held
has been called off

64
00:06:10.287 --> 00:06:12.205
and the German police
are retreating from the area.

65
00:06:12.289 --> 00:06:14.291
Officials seem to have decided
to abandon their plans

66
00:06:14.374 --> 00:06:16.501
when the leader of the fedayeen
came out of the building

67
00:06:16.626 --> 00:06:18.169
and demanded they call off the siege.

68
00:06:18.295 --> 00:06:19.671
pointing out that the entire operation

69
00:06:19.796 --> 00:06:20.922
was being watched on a television set

70
00:06:21.006 --> 00:06:22.132
within the apartment.

71
00:06:22.215 --> 00:06:24.551
Apparently. new demands have
been made to move the fedayeen

72
00:06:24.634 --> 00:06:26.720
and their hostages.
though it isn't yet known

73
00:06:26.803 --> 00:06:28.305
when or where this might occur.

74
00:06:28.388 --> 00:06:32.309
This is Peter. Do you have something
to report to us from where you are?

75
00:06:32.392 --> 00:06:34.978
This is Cosell. I certainly do. Peter.

76
00:06:35.061 --> 00:06:38.106
We have an immense flurry
of action here.

77
00:06:38.189 --> 00:06:42.068
Suddenly. in the whole area between
building 20 and building 12

78
00:06:43.028 --> 00:06:44.988
they have been clearing out cars.

79
00:06:45.071 --> 00:06:48.241
Obviously wary of an assault
from the German police...

80
00:07:02.255 --> 00:07:03.715
... within five minutes.

81
00:07:03.840 --> 00:07:05.383
What I'm hearing from here is that

82
00:07:05.508 --> 00:07:09.012
they're heading to an airport
called Fiirstenfeldbruck.

83
00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:10.722
...says the chopper just landed

84
00:07:10.847 --> 00:07:12.098
at the back of the Olympic village here.

85
00:07:12.182 --> 00:07:13.892
Can you see gate number seven?

86
00:07:14.017 --> 00:07:19.564
This is Vance Kolvig. What I have seen
are four hostages in one helicopter

87
00:07:19.689 --> 00:07:23.026
and it looks like five hostages
in the first helicopter.

88
00:07:23.109 --> 00:07:27.072
Yes. I just got back a little while ago
and it was obvious that something

89
00:07:27.197 --> 00:07:28.531
quite serious was going on out there.

90
00:07:28.615 --> 00:07:30.992
Here we are. outside the gates.
There are armoured cars

91
00:07:31.076 --> 00:07:32.369
police cars...

92
00:07:33.036 --> 00:07:35.664
Police are pouring in through
the gates with lights flashing

93
00:07:35.747 --> 00:07:37.999
and here come some more.
Five. six. here comes another one.

94
00:07:38.083 --> 00:07:40.418
Seven armoured cars
have gone in through the gates now.

95
00:07:40.543 --> 00:07:42.170
They re mounting a major invasion.

96
00:07:42.253 --> 00:07:44.255
The latest word we get
from the airport is that

97
00:07:45.548 --> 00:07:47.384
quote. "All hell has broken loose
out there."

98
00:08:03.400 --> 00:08:05.318
It's just arrived. Peter.
The bus has arrived

99
00:08:05.402 --> 00:08:07.445
- to the helicopters.
- We have reports now

100
00:08:07.570 --> 00:08:11.241
that all the hostages.
all nine hostages are safe.

101
00:08:11.616 --> 00:08:15.620
We repeat. we have confirmed.
it's just past 1:00 a.m.

102
00:08:15.745 --> 00:08:17.455
The fighting ceased at midnight.

103
00:08:17.580 --> 00:08:19.582
Well. that's at least 24 we've seen go in

104
00:08:19.666 --> 00:08:21.126
and now we can see
the lights flashing...

105
00:08:21.251 --> 00:08:23.878
There was a terrible battle
at the airport. but the hostages

106
00:08:23.962 --> 00:08:26.464
somehow the hostages are safe.

107
00:08:26.589 --> 00:08:29.092
And. according to these reports.
all Arab terrorists

108
00:08:29.175 --> 00:08:30.885
have died by German gunfire.

109
00:08:30.969 --> 00:08:33.972
Originally it was said
that the hostages were safe

110
00:08:34.097 --> 00:08:36.141
but now that has been changed.

111
00:08:36.266 --> 00:08:38.435
An Olympic spokesman said that...

112
00:08:38.518 --> 00:08:40.562
Of the areas in the world.
this is one of the areas...

113
00:08:40.645 --> 00:08:42.939
Who is telling the families?

114
00:08:43.606 --> 00:08:45.775
Then someone should tell them.

115
00:08:46.443 --> 00:08:48.319
They've spent their youth.
their young people.

116
00:08:48.445 --> 00:08:49.821
they've spent all their money on wars.

117
00:08:49.946 --> 00:08:52.657
Now they have a chance to build
their nations. These nations...

118
00:08:52.782 --> 00:08:55.326
And. of course. they're compatible.
The Arabs and the Israelis

119
00:08:55.452 --> 00:08:57.203
are perfectly compatible
as far as I can tell.

120
00:08:57.287 --> 00:08:59.122
And now. as you say. Peter.
you're quite right.

121
00:08:59.205 --> 00:09:01.416
They've been jolted apart again.
as they were

122
00:09:01.499 --> 00:09:04.335
seeming to come just a little
closer. Little hope.

123
00:09:04.461 --> 00:09:06.880
We've just gotten the final word.
When I was a kid.

124
00:09:06.963 --> 00:09:09.549
my father used to say our greatest
hopes and our worst fears

125
00:09:09.632 --> 00:09:13.136
are seldom realised. Our worst fears
have been realised tonight.

126
00:09:13.219 --> 00:09:16.014
They've now said
that there were 11 hostages.

127
00:09:16.139 --> 00:09:18.641
Two were killed in their rooms

128
00:09:19.517 --> 00:09:21.227
yesterday morning.

129
00:09:21.478 --> 00:09:25.690
Nine were killed at the airport tonight.

130
00:09:25.982 --> 00:09:27.525
They're all gone.

131
00:09:28.485 --> 00:09:30.862
...before a quiet crowd of 80.000.

132
00:09:30.987 --> 00:09:33.114
After the ceremony. the surviving team

133
00:09:33.198 --> 00:09:35.200
saw the coffins of their fallen comrades

134
00:09:35.325 --> 00:09:38.036
loaded onto an airplane
to bring them home together.

135
00:09:38.161 --> 00:09:40.705
Enormous crowds also gathered
on Dizengoff Street

136
00:09:40.830 --> 00:09:44.167
and in Jerusalem on the plaza
in front of the Knesset.

137
00:09:44.334 --> 00:09:46.961
People are weeping.
tearing their clothes.

138
00:09:47.045 --> 00:09:49.714
The funerals. which will be held
tomorrow in Jerusalem.

139
00:09:49.839 --> 00:09:52.717
are expected to draw
tens of thousands of mourners.

140
00:09:52.842 --> 00:09:55.220
These are the names of the members
of the Israeli team

141
00:09:55.345 --> 00:09:57.639
at the Munich Olympics.
who were held hostage.

142
00:09:57.722 --> 00:10:01.017
beaten. and finally murdered
by Arab terrorists.

143
00:10:08.608 --> 00:10:10.401
Dr Wadi Haddad.

144
00:10:11.111 --> 00:10:12.403
Abu Daoud.

145
00:10:12.946 --> 00:10:14.114
Mahmoud Hamshari.

146
00:10:19.953 --> 00:10:21.412
Wael Zwaiter.

147
00:10:21.913 --> 00:10:23.748
Dr Basil al-Kubaisi.

148
00:10:24.374 --> 00:10:25.458
Kamal Nasser.

149
00:10:31.798 --> 00:10:33.258
Kemal Adwan.

150
00:10:34.134 --> 00:10:35.552
Abu Youssef.

151
00:10:35.844 --> 00:10:36.845
Mohammed Boudia.

152
00:10:40.723 --> 00:10:42.267
Hussein al-Chir.

153
00:10:42.392 --> 00:10:43.935
Ali Hassan Salameh.

154
00:10:47.772 --> 00:10:50.900
As all of Israel mourns.
of course everyone says prayers

155
00:10:50.984 --> 00:10:52.068
for the people...

156
00:10:52.152 --> 00:10:54.904
I tried not to think about you.
but I couldn't.

157
00:10:54.988 --> 00:10:58.783
...a very private. terrible grief
in the days and years to come.

158
00:10:59.075 --> 00:11:03.121
I have the world's most boring job.
What's going to happen to me?

159
00:11:03.454 --> 00:11:06.040
Well. they were just athletes.
They went to the Olympics.

160
00:11:06.124 --> 00:11:08.084
Look what happened to them.

161
00:11:10.795 --> 00:11:12.088
What now?

162
00:11:14.632 --> 00:11:16.926
Now we're going to have a baby.

163
00:11:19.637 --> 00:11:21.097
Eleven names.

164
00:11:21.639 --> 00:11:24.767
Give us the order. and we'll begin.

165
00:11:28.605 --> 00:11:30.523
It's the same as Eichmann.

166
00:11:31.816 --> 00:11:33.318
We say to these butchers.

167
00:11:33.443 --> 00:11:35.278
"You didn't want to share
this world with us.

168
00:11:35.361 --> 00:11:38.281
"then we don't have
to share this world with you."

169
00:11:39.449 --> 00:11:42.202
There's legitimacy for this.
Am I correct?

170
00:11:45.496 --> 00:11:47.832
Ambushed and slaughtered again.

171
00:11:49.834 --> 00:11:53.296
while the rest of the world
is playing games. Olympic torches

172
00:11:53.379 --> 00:11:56.174
and brass bands
and dead Jews in Germany.

173
00:11:56.799 --> 00:11:58.885
And the world couldn't care less.

174
00:11:58.968 --> 00:12:01.054
We've responded.
We sent 70 fighter jets.

175
00:12:01.137 --> 00:12:02.305
A response no one heard.

176
00:12:02.388 --> 00:12:04.933
Air strikes on guerrilla
training centres. That's a response.

177
00:12:05.016 --> 00:12:06.935
No one notices what happens
in the border camps.

178
00:12:07.018 --> 00:12:09.687
Sixty Arabs dead. at least.
Who knows how many wounded.

179
00:12:09.812 --> 00:12:12.190
This is about fixing the world's attention.

180
00:12:12.315 --> 00:12:14.859
Well. it's not just a publicity stunt.

181
00:12:15.026 --> 00:12:16.694
Let me remind you.

182
00:12:17.153 --> 00:12:21.157
Ali Hassan Salameh.
he invented Black September.

183
00:12:21.366 --> 00:12:24.160
He is the architect
of the Munich murders.

184
00:12:25.370 --> 00:12:26.871
These people.

185
00:12:27.705 --> 00:12:29.874
They're sworn to destroy us.

186
00:12:32.335 --> 00:12:34.212
Forget peace for now.

187
00:12:34.712 --> 00:12:37.173
We have to show them we're strong.

188
00:12:37.882 --> 00:12:40.760
We have laws. we represent civilisation.

189
00:12:41.511 --> 00:12:44.138
Some people say
we can't afford to be civilised.

190
00:12:44.222 --> 00:12:46.557
I've always resisted such people.

191
00:12:47.767 --> 00:12:50.019
But I don't know who these maniacs are

192
00:12:50.103 --> 00:12:52.063
and where they come from.

193
00:12:53.356 --> 00:12:54.774
Palestinians?

194
00:12:55.233 --> 00:12:57.193
They're not recognisable.

195
00:13:00.280 --> 00:13:03.574
You tell me what law
protects people like these.

196
00:13:06.869 --> 00:13:09.122
Today I'm hearing with new ears.

197
00:13:10.748 --> 00:13:13.209
Every civilisation finds it necessary

198
00:13:13.293 --> 00:13:17.046
to negotiate compromises
with its own values.

199
00:13:19.924 --> 00:13:21.759
I've made a decision.

200
00:13:21.884 --> 00:13:24.262
The responsibility is entirely mine.

201
00:13:32.645 --> 00:13:34.397
- Avner?
- Yes?

202
00:13:34.480 --> 00:13:36.774
We're going to Jerusalem. Get in.

203
00:13:38.735 --> 00:13:40.236
Come on. Sir.

204
00:13:48.661 --> 00:13:50.913
Hello. I'm General Zamir.

205
00:13:51.289 --> 00:13:52.415
Yes.

206
00:13:52.999 --> 00:13:54.625
You swore us in.

207
00:13:54.751 --> 00:13:56.961
My unit. when I joined Mossad.

208
00:13:57.086 --> 00:13:58.796
I don't remember you.

209
00:14:00.006 --> 00:14:02.175
Of course. I know your father.

210
00:14:12.268 --> 00:14:13.436
Avner.

211
00:14:15.313 --> 00:14:18.441
- It's been...
- Two years since I worked for you.

212
00:14:18.649 --> 00:14:21.152
I remember. Please. sit down.

213
00:14:22.487 --> 00:14:23.780
Harari.

214
00:14:24.614 --> 00:14:26.115
General Nadav.

215
00:14:26.824 --> 00:14:28.493
And General Yariv.

216
00:14:29.285 --> 00:14:31.496
How are you? How is your father?

217
00:14:31.621 --> 00:14:33.331
He's fine. Thank you.

218
00:14:35.333 --> 00:14:38.419
Coffee? It's wonderful to see you again.

219
00:14:38.503 --> 00:14:39.629
Sit.

220
00:14:42.673 --> 00:14:44.842
The chief of the Mossad. two generals

221
00:14:44.967 --> 00:14:47.845
and the Prime Minister.
Obviously. it's important.

222
00:14:50.348 --> 00:14:52.183
This is something new.

223
00:14:52.350 --> 00:14:54.977
What happened in Munich
changes everything.

224
00:14:57.397 --> 00:15:00.691
We want to ask you.
Will you undertake a mission?

225
00:15:01.401 --> 00:15:04.612
An important mission. You will
have to leave the country

226
00:15:04.695 --> 00:15:06.989
and your family. maybe for years.

227
00:15:07.073 --> 00:15:09.992
- And it is dangerous.
- You can't talk about it to anyone.

228
00:15:10.076 --> 00:15:11.702
Not even your wife.

229
00:15:16.541 --> 00:15:18.709
Now you should say something.

230
00:15:19.836 --> 00:15:21.838
Do you have any questions?

231
00:15:23.923 --> 00:15:27.260
So. this isn't about
guarding tourists on El Al jets?

232
00:15:29.929 --> 00:15:31.389
No questions?

233
00:15:31.889 --> 00:15:34.350
Did we mention how dangerous it is?

234
00:15:34.892 --> 00:15:37.353
You know. my sister died on Tuesday.

235
00:15:37.728 --> 00:15:40.022
- No. I didn't know that.
- Cancer.

236
00:15:40.356 --> 00:15:42.733
I couldn't go to the athletes' funerals

237
00:15:42.859 --> 00:15:44.360
because she died.

238
00:15:46.028 --> 00:15:48.739
That upset people.
but she was my sister.

239
00:15:50.283 --> 00:15:51.868
Family matters.

240
00:15:56.372 --> 00:15:59.917
- Your wife is pregnant.
- Yes. seven months.

241
00:16:00.042 --> 00:16:01.210
Mazel tov.

242
00:16:02.044 --> 00:16:04.297
You were one of
my favourite bodyguards.

243
00:16:04.380 --> 00:16:07.091
You know. I like neat. durable men.

244
00:16:07.633 --> 00:16:10.428
You liked having
the son of a hero around.

245
00:16:12.221 --> 00:16:15.057
Truth be told. you don't look
much like your father.

246
00:16:15.141 --> 00:16:16.267
No?

247
00:16:18.394 --> 00:16:20.730
Your mother is who you resemble.

248
00:16:39.624 --> 00:16:41.250
Tomorrow morning.

249
00:16:41.792 --> 00:16:44.170
If you can't decide in one day.

250
00:16:45.004 --> 00:16:46.631
you can't decide.

251
00:16:56.599 --> 00:16:57.975
Her sister died.

252
00:16:58.100 --> 00:17:00.645
But I think she didn't go
to the athletes' funerals

253
00:17:00.770 --> 00:17:02.396
because some people are angry at her

254
00:17:02.480 --> 00:17:05.107
for not negotiating with the terrorists.

255
00:17:12.865 --> 00:17:14.367
She didn't go to the funerals

256
00:17:14.450 --> 00:17:16.702
because she didn't want to be booed.

257
00:17:16.786 --> 00:17:19.121
It's a good sign you didn't ask questions.

258
00:17:19.205 --> 00:17:20.581
You'll say yes.

259
00:17:20.665 --> 00:17:23.876
I'm your case officer.
My name is Ephraim.

260
00:17:49.569 --> 00:17:53.406
How late in the pregnancy
before you have to stop having sex?

261
00:17:55.741 --> 00:17:56.993
Labour.

262
00:18:11.007 --> 00:18:13.759
Don't worry about it.
You won't be around.

263
00:18:15.678 --> 00:18:16.887
Will you?

264
00:18:19.432 --> 00:18:21.976
Whatever they want.
make sure they give you a raise.

265
00:18:22.059 --> 00:18:24.103
I need things for the baby.

266
00:18:24.437 --> 00:18:26.689
I can't live with refusing this.

267
00:18:28.608 --> 00:18:31.360
Your mother.
she knew what she was doing.

268
00:18:31.944 --> 00:18:34.614
- She abandoned you on that kibbutz.
- She didn't abandon me.

269
00:18:34.697 --> 00:18:36.115
My father was missing.

270
00:18:36.198 --> 00:18:38.534
He was in prison.
she was overwhelmed.

271
00:18:38.618 --> 00:18:41.412
- Oh. yes.
- She did what anybody would do.

272
00:18:41.579 --> 00:18:44.874
Yeah. so she took you to the kibbutz
and abandoned you.

273
00:18:45.750 --> 00:18:48.252
Now you think Israel is your mother.

274
00:18:55.217 --> 00:18:56.552
So listen.

275
00:18:57.720 --> 00:19:00.723
I'm going to go along with this.
until I don't.

276
00:19:02.099 --> 00:19:04.977
- Do you understand me?
- I love you.

277
00:19:08.397 --> 00:19:10.566
I'm not the hero's nice wife.

278
00:19:16.739 --> 00:19:20.826
First you resign from Mossad.
Your new contract.

279
00:19:21.994 --> 00:19:25.039
It says we do not employ you.
offer you benefits. or pensions

280
00:19:25.122 --> 00:19:27.625
or legal aid or medical assistance.

281
00:19:27.917 --> 00:19:30.670
It's a contract that there is no contract.

282
00:19:31.420 --> 00:19:33.339
- Do I get a copy?
- You don't.

283
00:19:33.422 --> 00:19:35.758
Your pension contribution refund.

284
00:19:36.342 --> 00:19:38.469
You're now officially unofficial.

285
00:19:38.594 --> 00:19:40.513
Unemployed and uninsured.

286
00:19:42.098 --> 00:19:43.641
You'll open two accounts

287
00:19:43.766 --> 00:19:46.018
at the Union de Banques Suisse
in Geneva

288
00:19:46.102 --> 00:19:47.561
on Rue du Commerce.

289
00:19:47.645 --> 00:19:51.190
Operational funds in one box.
in the other your salary

290
00:19:51.273 --> 00:19:53.442
which you don't take
till the mission ends

291
00:19:53.526 --> 00:19:55.194
when you get what accumulates.

292
00:19:55.277 --> 00:19:58.114
Also. for each of your men. you open
an account for his salary.

293
00:19:58.197 --> 00:20:02.201
- How many men do I have for this...
- In the operational funds box

294
00:20:02.284 --> 00:20:06.038
we will deposit 250.000
American dollars.

295
00:20:06.622 --> 00:20:09.375
You take it out. we put more in.

296
00:20:09.500 --> 00:20:11.711
I want receipts.

297
00:20:12.002 --> 00:20:14.004
You are not working
for the Baron Rothschild.

298
00:20:14.130 --> 00:20:16.382
You're working for Israel.
a small country.

299
00:20:16.465 --> 00:20:19.969
I'm an old Galicianer
from a mud hut in the Ukraine.

300
00:20:20.052 --> 00:20:22.638
And I don't trust Yekke putzes
let loose in Europe

301
00:20:22.722 --> 00:20:24.890
with unlimited operational expenses.

302
00:20:24.974 --> 00:20:27.393
I was born in Israel. I'm not a Yekke.

303
00:20:27.476 --> 00:20:30.146
- Where is your grandpa from?
- Frankfurt.

304
00:20:30.646 --> 00:20:32.231
You're a Yekke.

305
00:20:32.523 --> 00:20:36.569
Your wife receives monthly $1.000
in her bank account.

306
00:20:36.902 --> 00:20:40.406
Also. we leave messages in the box
with the operational funds.

307
00:20:40.656 --> 00:20:42.658
You can leave messages for us.

308
00:20:43.409 --> 00:20:47.163
- But there shouldn't be messages.
- I don't care about that.

309
00:20:47.747 --> 00:20:51.500
- Bring me receipts. you got me?
- I got you.

310
00:20:51.876 --> 00:20:55.671
Whatever you are doing.
somebody else is paying for it.

311
00:20:59.341 --> 00:21:01.218
We have 11 Palestinian names.

312
00:21:01.343 --> 00:21:03.304
Each had a hand in planning Munich.

313
00:21:03.387 --> 00:21:06.223
You're going to kill them.
11 men. one by one.

314
00:21:06.348 --> 00:21:07.558
They're all in Europe now.

315
00:21:07.683 --> 00:21:09.101
You'll stay there as long as it takes.

316
00:21:09.185 --> 00:21:12.271
Europe only. not the Arab countries.
That's for us. not you.

317
00:21:12.354 --> 00:21:14.482
And not Eastern Bloc.
Don't upset the Russians.

318
00:21:14.565 --> 00:21:16.025
Who needs it?

319
00:21:17.067 --> 00:21:19.361
You'll have no contact with us.

320
00:21:19.737 --> 00:21:22.239
You're not going to give me
any information?

321
00:21:22.364 --> 00:21:24.742
We deposit money
from a fund that doesn't exist

322
00:21:24.867 --> 00:21:27.870
into a box we don't know about.
in a bank we never set foot in.

323
00:21:27.953 --> 00:21:30.498
We can't help you because
we never heard of you before.

324
00:21:30.581 --> 00:21:32.291
You'll do what the terrorists do.

325
00:21:32.374 --> 00:21:35.628
You think they report back
to home base? They don't.

326
00:21:36.253 --> 00:21:37.880
We want them dead.

327
00:21:38.714 --> 00:21:41.133
Nothing better than
eating something sweet by the sea.

328
00:21:41.217 --> 00:21:43.135
You can ask questions now.

329
00:21:43.219 --> 00:21:45.137
- Am I alone?
- Four others.

330
00:21:45.471 --> 00:21:48.307
They know useful things
like cars. documents.

331
00:21:48.390 --> 00:21:50.893
cleanup to make sure you don't
accidentally drop your fake passport

332
00:21:50.976 --> 00:21:53.813
next to the dead body.
You're the team leader.

333
00:21:56.440 --> 00:21:59.151
- Who kills the targets?
- You do. Who else?

334
00:21:59.443 --> 00:22:01.904
Use guns if you have to.
but the bombs are preferable.

335
00:22:01.987 --> 00:22:04.031
One of your guys knows
how to make them.

336
00:22:04.114 --> 00:22:07.409
We want everyone to read in Le Monde
some famous Arab terrorist is dead.

337
00:22:07.493 --> 00:22:09.078
Who knows who blew him up?

338
00:22:09.161 --> 00:22:11.580
- Why me?
- So what's wrong with you?

339
00:22:11.914 --> 00:22:14.500
I'm not an experienced field operative.

340
00:22:15.167 --> 00:22:18.003
- So I'm not known.
- Not even I know you now.

341
00:22:18.504 --> 00:22:20.714
And also. I lived in Frankfurt
when I was a kid

342
00:22:20.798 --> 00:22:23.092
so I'm a Yekke Jew
who knows his way around Europe.

343
00:22:23.175 --> 00:22:26.428
That's a good reason.
Here's one more. You're ordinary.

344
00:22:26.512 --> 00:22:28.514
You aren't a sabra Charles Bronson.

345
00:22:28.597 --> 00:22:30.349
- ] am a sabra.
- I know.

346
00:22:30.432 --> 00:22:32.810
I know so much about you.
You're a nice sabra

347
00:22:32.935 --> 00:22:35.896
with a dog and a baby on the way.
You won't shoot Spanish bellhops.

348
00:22:35.980 --> 00:22:37.982
No bellhops. No civilians.

349
00:22:38.107 --> 00:22:40.359
That kind of trouble we can't afford.

350
00:22:40.442 --> 00:22:42.862
The hard thing will not be finding them.

351
00:22:42.945 --> 00:22:44.947
Some of them. anyway.
are not so carefully hidden.

352
00:22:45.030 --> 00:22:47.449
The hard thing will be
not punishing yourselves

353
00:22:47.533 --> 00:22:49.869
by getting caught or getting killed.

354
00:22:49.952 --> 00:22:52.621
- You want the last piece of baklava?
- No.

355
00:22:52.705 --> 00:22:54.874
Smart decision.
You should avoid sweets.

356
00:22:54.957 --> 00:22:58.294
After all. you just signed away
your dental insurance.

357
00:23:00.212 --> 00:23:02.715
This is Pierre Bouchet.
your captain. speaking.

358
00:23:02.798 --> 00:23:06.385
Welcome aboard Flight SA 74
direct to Geneva.

359
00:23:06.468 --> 00:23:09.722
We are now at a cruising altitude
of 30.000 feet

360
00:23:09.805 --> 00:23:12.224
and we wish you a pleasant flight.

361
00:23:57.394 --> 00:24:00.397
Don't shoot. I don't understand
what you're saying.

362
00:24:23.754 --> 00:24:25.714
Easy. easy. easy.

363
00:26:19.536 --> 00:26:21.747
Press the buzzer when you're done.

364
00:26:40.349 --> 00:26:42.518
- Have a nice day.
- Thank you.

365
00:26:47.064 --> 00:26:48.732
I'm not good at it. No.

366
00:26:48.857 --> 00:26:50.150
- Hebrew?
- No.

367
00:26:50.234 --> 00:26:52.361
A team leader who cooks.
What a luxury.

368
00:26:52.444 --> 00:26:54.738
- Years in the kibbutz kitchen.
- You've done this before?

369
00:26:54.863 --> 00:26:56.115
Done what?

370
00:26:56.240 --> 00:26:57.783
Sit. Come on.

371
00:26:58.867 --> 00:27:02.121
Because I joined Mossad
10 minutes ago. and I'm...

372
00:27:03.789 --> 00:27:06.917
Look. I want to kill
every one of these pigs. but...

373
00:27:07.960 --> 00:27:09.169
Thank you.

374
00:27:09.253 --> 00:27:11.964
So. some of you
have training in this kind of...

375
00:27:12.047 --> 00:27:14.133
- He sells antiques.
- Right here in Frankfurt.

376
00:27:14.216 --> 00:27:15.968
It's a front. but successful.

377
00:27:16.051 --> 00:27:18.053
I'm a documents
and identities specialist

378
00:27:18.137 --> 00:27:20.806
with a sharp eye
for early Danish Modern.

379
00:27:21.723 --> 00:27:22.891
And you?

380
00:27:23.559 --> 00:27:25.144
Oh. I make toys.

381
00:27:25.394 --> 00:27:28.564
- I thought you made bombs.
- Toys. in Brussels.

382
00:27:29.064 --> 00:27:31.441
For bombs. I had to go to night school.

383
00:27:31.650 --> 00:27:33.485
My wife's expecting.

384
00:27:33.569 --> 00:27:35.195
- Mazel tov.
- Mazel tov.

385
00:27:35.279 --> 00:27:37.823
- Beautiful. When?
- Couple of months.

386
00:27:38.824 --> 00:27:40.909
Think we'll be done by then?

387
00:27:41.577 --> 00:27:44.079
Is it Ali Hassan Salameh we're after?

388
00:27:46.331 --> 00:27:48.584
I mean. that's the job. right?

389
00:27:49.084 --> 00:27:52.588
We're here to kill the guy
who planned Munich. Am I right?

390
00:27:55.257 --> 00:27:59.261
It's strange. isn't it.
to think of oneself as an assassin?

391
00:27:59.344 --> 00:28:01.763
Think of yourself
as something else then.

392
00:28:01.847 --> 00:28:06.310
- A soldier in a war.
- I mean. you know how to shoot.

393
00:28:07.311 --> 00:28:09.980
to assassinate people. right?

394
00:28:11.106 --> 00:28:12.774
Mazels on the baby. and all that.
That's great.

395
00:28:12.858 --> 00:28:15.194
That's just fantastic. But. I mean...

396
00:28:16.778 --> 00:28:19.031
You make dolls in a toy shop

397
00:28:20.032 --> 00:28:23.202
and you shop for sofas

398
00:28:23.619 --> 00:28:25.370
and you. I don't know what you do.

399
00:28:25.454 --> 00:28:27.623
Me? [ worry.

400
00:28:28.498 --> 00:28:30.918
So. why'd they make you team leader?

401
00:28:31.001 --> 00:28:33.712
Because he really knows
how to cook a brisket.

402
00:29:00.822 --> 00:29:02.491
- Hello?
- Andreas.

403
00:29:02.991 --> 00:29:05.160
- Surprised?
Surprised? You punched me.

404
00:29:05.244 --> 00:29:07.246
- You broke my jaw. man.
- That was 10 years ago.

405
00:29:07.329 --> 00:29:09.498
And you were sleeping
with my girlfriend.

406
00:29:09.581 --> 00:29:11.500
Listen. I'm in town. Are you around?

407
00:29:11.583 --> 00:29:13.418
Yeah. actually.
I'm here with my girlfriend.

408
00:29:13.502 --> 00:29:15.921
- Do you want to come over?
- Perfect.

409
00:29:19.508 --> 00:29:22.636
Should one look at right and
wrong as ethical questions?

410
00:29:23.178 --> 00:29:24.680
That is the problem.

411
00:29:26.181 --> 00:29:30.686
Marcuse says Hegel's "Philosophy of Right"
does not assign a moral category to "wrong."

412
00:29:31.019 --> 00:29:37.484
Free will inevitably causes wrong.
That's written by Marx. The blind anarchy of capitalism.

413
00:29:37.693 --> 00:29:41.280
You have to be prepared to
reconsider right and wrong.

414
00:29:41.530 --> 00:29:47.035
Because basically those are just terms that express a
horrible struggle. parts of an equation of pure dialectic.

415
00:29:47.202 --> 00:29:50.872
- She's incredible. isn't she?
- I have no idea what she's talking about.

416
00:29:52.624 --> 00:29:56.670
So are you Baader-Meinhof? Red Army Faction?
What?

417
00:29:58.213 --> 00:29:59.131
At least.

418
00:29:59.923 --> 00:30:01.550
You don't read much huh?

419
00:30:03.552 --> 00:30:04.636
What's your business?

420
00:30:05.762 --> 00:30:08.265
I work for some Americans.

421
00:30:09.099 --> 00:30:11.143
Rich Americans. right?

422
00:30:16.815 --> 00:30:21.111
Yvonne. I think Avner wants to go to bed with you.

423
00:30:24.239 --> 00:30:27.534
I miss you. man.
We really used to love each other.

424
00:30:27.617 --> 00:30:30.746
That was a long time ago.
We were in high school.

425
00:30:33.290 --> 00:30:35.000
That's sixty thousand dollars.

426
00:30:35.459 --> 00:30:37.085
I have some names.

427
00:30:37.169 --> 00:30:40.756
Some people I need to find
for my rich American friends.

428
00:30:44.259 --> 00:30:46.136
Give me my money. Yvonne.

429
00:30:48.430 --> 00:30:51.308
- One hundred fifty.
- One hundred.

430
00:30:51.767 --> 00:30:52.934
Cash.

431
00:30:53.101 --> 00:30:54.770
$100.000.

432
00:30:58.440 --> 00:31:01.318
These people I'm looking for.
you don't know them.

433
00:31:02.027 --> 00:31:04.446
- We might.
- You don't.

434
00:31:05.947 --> 00:31:08.158
But maybe you know
someone who does.

435
00:31:08.950 --> 00:31:11.286
And it's Americans you work for?

436
00:31:11.787 --> 00:31:13.538
Yes. See?

437
00:31:14.289 --> 00:31:15.791
James Madison.

438
00:31:16.708 --> 00:31:18.377
Americans.

439
00:31:18.835 --> 00:31:20.629
We'll ask some friends.

440
00:31:21.797 --> 00:31:24.007
Hiding? The Arabs are not hiding.

441
00:31:24.132 --> 00:31:26.468
Munich was a big success for them.

442
00:31:26.635 --> 00:31:28.345
The implications of Munich
for the struggle...

443
00:31:28.470 --> 00:31:32.474
They got everyone's attention.
They're recruiting. making plans.

444
00:31:32.974 --> 00:31:34.643
Give me a few names.

445
00:31:38.647 --> 00:31:41.441
I can't help if I don't know
who you're trying to find.

446
00:31:41.525 --> 00:31:43.318
We'll have to trust.

447
00:31:43.402 --> 00:31:45.487
You have to cross the line.

448
00:31:46.238 --> 00:31:49.741
I trust you. You carry cash
and you don't make speeches.

449
00:31:49.825 --> 00:31:52.702
Nowadays. everyone makes speeches.
like your friend Andreas.

450
00:31:52.828 --> 00:31:54.413
Talk. talk. talk.

451
00:31:55.205 --> 00:31:56.748
Name me an Arab.

452
00:32:00.836 --> 00:32:02.170
Abu Daoud.

453
00:32:02.671 --> 00:32:04.005
Abu Youssef.

454
00:32:04.548 --> 00:32:06.007
Wael Zwaiter.

455
00:32:07.008 --> 00:32:08.427
Kamal Nasser.

456
00:32:10.512 --> 00:32:12.431
- Salameh.
- Forget Salameh. Too hard.

457
00:32:12.514 --> 00:32:15.350
Wait. Who are these guys?
Why are you trying to find Arabs?

458
00:32:15.434 --> 00:32:18.019
Sixty thousand per name. Dollars.

459
00:32:18.520 --> 00:32:22.023
- If it's good information.
- If it isn't good. it doesn't cost.

460
00:32:22.190 --> 00:32:24.359
Wael Zwaiter's here. in Rome.

461
00:32:25.110 --> 00:32:28.405
He just translated
the Arabian Nights into Italian.

462
00:32:28.613 --> 00:32:31.741
Tomorrow there's a reading. He's broke.

463
00:32:32.033 --> 00:32:34.578
He has a niece he calls every day
in Damascus.

464
00:32:34.703 --> 00:32:36.913
Are you trying to join the PLO?

465
00:32:37.539 --> 00:32:39.458
We need to talk. Alone.

466
00:32:41.543 --> 00:32:44.212
And also maybe you need people
to help with your work.

467
00:32:44.296 --> 00:32:45.672
Cars. Vans.

468
00:32:45.755 --> 00:32:49.050
Listen. don't trust him okay.

469
00:32:49.593 --> 00:32:51.219
I heard that he is dangerous.

470
00:32:51.636 --> 00:32:54.973
Go! I don't want you to get hurt.

471
00:32:55.390 --> 00:32:56.808
Hurt. how?

472
00:32:58.894 --> 00:33:02.230
If you tell anybody about this.
I don't know.

473
00:33:03.398 --> 00:33:04.774
Just don't.

474
00:33:05.400 --> 00:33:06.735
Just don't.

475
00:33:24.920 --> 00:33:27.339
Anything you need. we'll provide.

476
00:33:28.089 --> 00:33:29.591
I need receipts.

477
00:34:01.790 --> 00:34:04.626
What attracts me to the Scheherazade story.

478
00:34:05.043 --> 00:34:09.631
to what you in the West call "The Arabian Nights" -

479
00:34:10.131 --> 00:34:12.968
- well am not an Arab. I am Palestinian.

480
00:34:13.802 --> 00:34:18.181
And why has a Palestinian poet worked for years

481
00:34:18.473 --> 00:34:21.851
translating 1.001 Arabian Nights
from Arabic into Italian?

482
00:34:22.477 --> 00:34:27.315
Apart from the expectation of
enormous riches. I mean.

483
00:34:28.233 --> 00:34:31.319
I love what this classic tells
about the power of narrative.

484
00:34:35.490 --> 00:34:39.369
the relationship of narrative to survival.

485
00:34:46.376 --> 00:34:48.753
Keep talking. Keep talking.

486
00:35:21.202 --> 00:35:23.246
Thank you for coming. Thank you.

487
00:38:26.262 --> 00:38:28.056
Are you Wael Zwaiter?

488
00:38:28.723 --> 00:38:30.475
Yes. and who are you?

489
00:38:35.063 --> 00:38:37.065
Do you know why we're here?

490
00:38:42.111 --> 00:38:44.781
- Are you Wael Zwaiter?
- He said yes already.

491
00:38:44.906 --> 00:38:46.574
He already said yes.

492
00:38:49.244 --> 00:38:50.745
What are we doing?

493
00:38:55.166 --> 00:38:56.626
What do I do?

494
00:38:57.252 --> 00:38:59.087
Do you know why we're here?

495
00:39:19.440 --> 00:39:20.984
What happened?
Why didn't you shoot him?

496
00:39:21.109 --> 00:39:22.610
- We shot him.
- But I didn't hear a shot.

497
00:39:22.694 --> 00:39:24.571
We shot him eight times.
maybe 10 times.

498
00:39:24.654 --> 00:39:26.281
- Did you kill him?
- He's dead.

499
00:39:26.364 --> 00:39:28.324
He shit his pants. He's dead.

500
00:40:15.997 --> 00:40:18.666
Drink some wine. We're celebrating.

501
00:40:19.334 --> 00:40:21.753
That old Pesach story.

502
00:40:22.670 --> 00:40:24.172
The angels are rejoicing

503
00:40:24.255 --> 00:40:27.759
because the Egyptians
have just drowned in the Red Sea.

504
00:40:29.344 --> 00:40:31.387
I didn't say we're rejoicing.

505
00:40:31.512 --> 00:40:33.681
I said. "We're celebrating."

506
00:40:33.765 --> 00:40:36.351
And God said to the angels.
"Why are you celebrating?

507
00:40:36.434 --> 00:40:38.978
"I've just killed a multitude
of my children."

508
00:40:39.062 --> 00:40:40.563
Mr Zwaiter.

509
00:40:41.356 --> 00:40:46.277
He cost us. by my calculations.
roughly $352.000.

510
00:40:48.696 --> 00:40:50.865
You didn't finish the story.

511
00:40:51.115 --> 00:40:53.201
The angels respond to God.

512
00:40:53.534 --> 00:40:55.244
They say. "God. we're celebrating

513
00:40:55.370 --> 00:40:57.956
"because when the people hear
what happened to the Egyptians

514
00:40:58.039 --> 00:40:59.540
"they'll understand your point."

515
00:40:59.624 --> 00:41:00.959
Which was?

516
00:41:01.918 --> 00:41:03.962
Don't fuck with the Jews.

517
00:41:05.213 --> 00:41:08.174
I don't know about the rest of you.
but I'm not celebrating.

518
00:41:08.257 --> 00:41:10.093
I'm goddamn rejoicing.

519
00:41:10.718 --> 00:41:13.346
Here. Put that down.
Put it down. Get up.

520
00:41:13.429 --> 00:41:15.056
- No. please.
- Come on. dance with me.

521
00:41:15.139 --> 00:41:17.308
- Dance with me. Come on.
- No.

522
00:41:17.558 --> 00:41:18.893
Come on.

523
00:41:20.979 --> 00:41:22.438
Come on. Hey.

524
00:41:55.430 --> 00:41:58.266
This is... What shall I call you today?

525
00:41:59.183 --> 00:42:00.685
Franz Storsch.

526
00:42:02.437 --> 00:42:04.313
You can call me Louis.

527
00:42:07.442 --> 00:42:10.361
- Our service has been satisfactory?
- Pricey.

528
00:42:13.114 --> 00:42:16.200
A Jew and a Frenchman.
We could haggle forever. huh?

529
00:42:16.284 --> 00:42:19.829
- I'm not a Jew.
- What do you suppose a ramson is?

530
00:42:20.121 --> 00:42:24.000
It's a kind of a wild leek.
Not in season. but garlic will do.

531
00:42:24.834 --> 00:42:27.670
My papa sometimes loses track
of the seasons.

532
00:42:27.795 --> 00:42:29.797
I know nothing about food.

533
00:42:30.465 --> 00:42:32.467
Why does he make me shop?

534
00:42:36.137 --> 00:42:38.681
You're wondering
if I'm French Intelligence.

535
00:42:38.806 --> 00:42:40.641
Or CIA or KGB.

536
00:42:41.059 --> 00:42:44.520
Or an agent with a profitable
sideline in information.

537
00:42:44.812 --> 00:42:47.815
I could be anybody.
You could be anybody. too.

538
00:42:48.191 --> 00:42:50.735
Identity. That's the boring part now.

539
00:42:52.361 --> 00:42:54.363
Here's what isn't boring.

540
00:42:55.198 --> 00:42:57.325
As long as you don't work
for any government...

541
00:42:57.408 --> 00:43:00.203
- I'm in private business.
- Rich Americans. I heard.

542
00:43:00.328 --> 00:43:02.997
I'm in private business. too. My family.

543
00:43:03.498 --> 00:43:08.002
We can locate almost anyone
for anyone anywhere

544
00:43:08.252 --> 00:43:10.838
and we are ideologically promiscuous.

545
00:43:10.922 --> 00:43:13.174
We love everybody. hate everybody.

546
00:43:13.257 --> 00:43:15.343
I get my feelings confused.

547
00:43:15.843 --> 00:43:18.012
If you're not working for any government.

548
00:43:18.096 --> 00:43:19.972
we know. or we find.

549
00:43:20.056 --> 00:43:22.266
we don't find. you don't pay.

550
00:43:23.351 --> 00:43:25.645
Initially it was the intention
of the hijackers

551
00:43:25.728 --> 00:43:29.148
to bring the Lufthansa
to Munich International Airport

552
00:43:29.232 --> 00:43:31.400
and then take onboard
the three prisoners

553
00:43:31.526 --> 00:43:34.737
at the end of the runway. where
Captain Klausen took his plane

554
00:43:34.862 --> 00:43:37.365
while an Arab held a hand grenade
at his head.

555
00:43:37.448 --> 00:43:38.825
Hey. Avner.

556
00:43:38.908 --> 00:43:41.661
A Lufthansa jet was hijacked
coming from Damascus.

557
00:43:41.744 --> 00:43:44.163
The hijackers demanded
the release of three killers

558
00:43:44.247 --> 00:43:45.414
who survived Munich

559
00:43:45.540 --> 00:43:47.792
and the Germans said yes. instantly.

560
00:43:47.875 --> 00:43:51.045
The Arabs would be flown
by private charter plane to Zagreb.

561
00:43:51.129 --> 00:43:53.047
Look. They're free now.

562
00:43:53.548 --> 00:43:54.882
They're in Libya.

563
00:44:02.557 --> 00:44:05.226
No qualms about rejoicing
on their side. eh?

564
00:44:05.935 --> 00:44:09.605
The Israeli kills the Arabs

565
00:44:10.731 --> 00:44:13.526
in Egypt. in Jordan. in Lebanon.
in Syria...

566
00:44:13.609 --> 00:44:15.069
Look at them.

567
00:44:16.237 --> 00:44:17.989
They're movie stars.

568
00:44:18.739 --> 00:44:21.742
But did you shoot
any of the Israeli hostages?

569
00:44:22.493 --> 00:44:27.415
It's not important to say
If I killed Israelis or not.

570
00:44:27.582 --> 00:44:29.500
We should go to Tripoli.

571
00:44:29.792 --> 00:44:31.085
Kill them.

572
00:44:31.335 --> 00:44:33.337
We don't go to Arab countries.

573
00:44:33.671 --> 00:44:36.090
We stick to the names
we've been given.

574
00:44:38.342 --> 00:44:40.011
Mahmoud Hamshari.

575
00:44:46.767 --> 00:44:48.769
Do you think. looking back on it now

576
00:44:48.853 --> 00:44:51.480
that you achieved anything
in the Munich operation?

577
00:44:51.606 --> 00:44:56.527
We have made our voice
heard by the world.

578
00:44:56.861 --> 00:44:58.529
Are those your words?

579
00:45:02.200 --> 00:45:03.492
The same thing again.

580
00:45:03.618 --> 00:45:07.705
They have made their voice heard
by the universe or the world

581
00:45:07.788 --> 00:45:09.874
who has not been hearing before.

582
00:45:13.294 --> 00:45:15.755
Well. I believe what he meant by this is

583
00:45:15.838 --> 00:45:18.549
that now the world will begin hearing us.

584
00:45:20.134 --> 00:45:24.722
We are. for 24 years. the world's
largest refugee population.

585
00:45:24.805 --> 00:45:26.891
Our homes taken from us.

586
00:45:26.974 --> 00:45:30.728
Living in camps. no future. no food.

587
00:45:30.811 --> 00:45:33.147
Nothing decent for our children.

588
00:45:33.814 --> 00:45:36.859
And. so was the attack
in Munich justified?

589
00:45:38.194 --> 00:45:40.655
The PLO condemns attacks on civilians.

590
00:45:40.738 --> 00:45:43.741
- Though for 24 years...
- Tell your newspaper that.

591
00:45:43.824 --> 00:45:47.578
...our civilians have been attacked
by the Israelis day after day...

592
00:45:47.662 --> 00:45:50.665
Tell them about all the years
and years of Palestinian blood

593
00:45:50.748 --> 00:45:53.084
spilled by Israel.
And who mourns for us?

594
00:45:53.167 --> 00:45:55.086
You know. Israel just bombed

595
00:45:55.169 --> 00:45:57.672
two refugee camps
in Syria and Lebanon.

596
00:45:57.755 --> 00:46:00.258
- Tell them that...
- 200 people killed.

597
00:46:00.508 --> 00:46:03.761
- Right after Munich they did this.
- It did not begin in Munich.

598
00:46:03.844 --> 00:46:06.722
And where does it end?
How will it ever end?

599
00:46:18.943 --> 00:46:22.154
I'm sorry. I need to use your phone.
I need to call my editor.

600
00:46:22.238 --> 00:46:23.864
Yes. yes. Sorry.

601
00:46:25.074 --> 00:46:27.618
- You see it. It's by the window.
- Thank you.

602
00:46:27.702 --> 00:46:29.370
This way. please.

603
00:48:31.242 --> 00:48:34.245
This man. we don't know
what he did specifically?

604
00:48:34.370 --> 00:48:37.623
Hamshari arranged the attempted
assassination of Ben-Gurion

605
00:48:37.706 --> 00:48:39.417
in Copenhagen a few years ago.

606
00:48:39.500 --> 00:48:41.252
Now he organises for Fatah in France.

607
00:48:41.335 --> 00:48:42.586
- He organises?
- Yes.

608
00:48:42.670 --> 00:48:44.463
In Tel Aviv they showed you
evidence for this?

609
00:48:44.547 --> 00:48:46.048
Not evidence. It was more

610
00:48:46.173 --> 00:48:47.925
this is the story and I believe them.

611
00:48:48.008 --> 00:48:49.552
Why? Don't you?

612
00:48:49.677 --> 00:48:52.513
It's a crisis. a war.
You don't have to always...

613
00:48:52.596 --> 00:48:55.724
- What? Be thinking?
- Scrutinise. Yeah. think.

614
00:48:55.850 --> 00:48:58.394
You want to wire Ephraim
and ask for evidence. you do it.

615
00:48:58.519 --> 00:49:00.187
You're on your own.

616
00:49:00.938 --> 00:49:02.731
- Okay. I'm done.
- Good.

617
00:49:02.857 --> 00:49:04.608
Don't think about it.

618
00:49:06.193 --> 00:49:07.278
Okay.

619
00:49:07.611 --> 00:49:11.282
So. now. I turn it on.

620
00:49:12.867 --> 00:49:15.911
He picks up the phone.
turns on the red light.

621
00:49:16.954 --> 00:49:20.040
then I take out the key. insert it.

622
00:49:20.583 --> 00:49:21.792
and turn.

623
00:50:25.439 --> 00:50:28.025
So now we wait for the red light.

624
00:50:56.345 --> 00:50:58.305
- Is the truck blocking the signal?
- No.

625
00:50:58.430 --> 00:51:00.474
Will the remote still work?

626
00:51:17.491 --> 00:51:19.952
- Yeah. it's a powerful transmitter.
- Go back to your position.

627
00:51:20.035 --> 00:51:22.663
You can't start improvising now.
Go back to your corner.

628
00:51:22.788 --> 00:51:25.332
Don't worry. It's okay. It's going to work.

629
00:52:55.089 --> 00:52:56.590
- Stop!
- Stop!

630
00:52:58.133 --> 00:52:59.468
Abort.

631
00:53:45.639 --> 00:53:47.266
Are we on or off?

632
00:54:04.867 --> 00:54:06.702
- Mahmoud Hamshari?
- Yes.

633
00:54:21.675 --> 00:54:23.802
He's at the hospital Cochin.

634
00:54:24.470 --> 00:54:27.055
I don't know how badly we hurt him.
They aren't saying.

635
00:54:27.181 --> 00:54:28.849
Why did you put a firecracker
in that phone?

636
00:54:28.974 --> 00:54:30.809
Because I didn't want
to blow up the building.

637
00:54:30.893 --> 00:54:33.353
- What do you want from me?
- An Arab corpse.

638
00:54:33.479 --> 00:54:36.815
Another $200.000. more or less.
to eliminate target number two.

639
00:54:36.899 --> 00:54:39.401
Yeah. if he's been eliminated.
We should stick with guns.

640
00:54:39.526 --> 00:54:41.445
No one notices a shooting.

641
00:54:41.528 --> 00:54:43.030
Bombs achieve a double objective.

642
00:54:43.155 --> 00:54:45.741
They eliminate targets
and they terrify terrorists.

643
00:54:45.866 --> 00:54:48.243
That only works when the bombs work.

644
00:54:48.368 --> 00:54:49.536
Lunch?

645
00:54:57.211 --> 00:55:00.172
The Israeli embassy in London
was rocked by a letter bomb

646
00:55:00.255 --> 00:55:02.341
shortly after 9:30 this morning.

647
00:55:02.424 --> 00:55:04.843
Dr Ami Shachori was opening
his morning mail

648
00:55:04.927 --> 00:55:08.055
when the envelope exploded.
killing him instantly.

649
00:55:08.180 --> 00:55:12.392
They discovered seven in a mailroom
near the embassy in Earls Court.

650
00:55:13.018 --> 00:55:15.854
- I1 guess they missed one.
- Right after Hanukkah.

651
00:55:16.396 --> 00:55:19.900
I guess there was a big pileup
of mail and they got careless.

652
00:55:20.526 --> 00:55:22.820
They found other letters in Israel.
of course.

653
00:55:22.903 --> 00:55:26.907
Canada. Argentina. Vienna.
Kinshasa. Paris. Brussels.

654
00:55:27.074 --> 00:55:30.244
Dozens of them.
mainly posted in the Netherlands.

655
00:55:30.911 --> 00:55:32.621
It's all Black September.

656
00:55:32.913 --> 00:55:34.748
It's a response. then.

657
00:55:35.082 --> 00:55:36.583
To Hamshari.

658
00:55:36.708 --> 00:55:38.252
And to Zwaiter.

659
00:55:39.253 --> 00:55:41.922
They're talking to us.
We're in dialogue now.

660
00:55:43.215 --> 00:55:44.633
Where are you?

661
00:55:46.093 --> 00:55:48.470
I'm in New York. following a lead.

662
00:55:48.929 --> 00:55:50.597
I'll call again.

663
00:56:01.942 --> 00:56:04.152
Are you going to visit your father?

664
00:56:05.779 --> 00:56:07.823
Why is this taking so long?

665
00:56:07.948 --> 00:56:09.449
It isn't fast.

666
00:56:10.242 --> 00:56:12.619
We have the best hospitals in the world.

667
00:56:13.787 --> 00:56:17.457
When you were born. your father
was elsewhere. I was alone.

668
00:56:18.667 --> 00:56:20.294
He was in prison.

669
00:56:22.921 --> 00:56:24.631
Should you be here?

670
00:56:25.007 --> 00:56:26.800
Aren't you on duty?

671
00:56:27.342 --> 00:56:29.928
What are you going to do? Turn me in?

672
00:56:31.680 --> 00:56:33.015
How is he?

673
00:56:33.932 --> 00:56:36.101
I don't visit your father so much.

674
00:56:36.184 --> 00:56:38.729
Wilma lets him yell at her all the time.

675
00:56:38.812 --> 00:56:40.480
She depresses me.

676
00:56:45.986 --> 00:56:47.362
How are you?

677
00:56:48.697 --> 00:56:51.491
I'm managing. Don't worry about me.

678
00:56:55.829 --> 00:56:58.165
I'm proud of what you are doing.

679
00:56:58.790 --> 00:57:01.001
You don't know what I'm doing.

680
00:57:11.136 --> 00:57:15.182
I look at you and I know
everything I need to know.

681
00:57:17.851 --> 00:57:19.853
She is frighteningly ugly.

682
00:57:20.646 --> 00:57:22.397
She takes after you.

683
00:57:23.482 --> 00:57:25.734
I want you to move. for a time.

684
00:57:25.984 --> 00:57:28.445
I've arranged a place for us in Brooklyn.

685
00:57:28.528 --> 00:57:30.739
I can't come back to Israel.
I don't know how long for...

686
00:57:30.864 --> 00:57:31.949
New York?

687
00:57:32.032 --> 00:57:35.160
- I can see more of you this way.
- New York City?

688
00:57:37.704 --> 00:57:41.041
But I have my family here.
and your parents.

689
00:57:42.209 --> 00:57:44.753
You want my parents to help raise her?

690
00:57:45.045 --> 00:57:47.047
Look what they did to me.

691
00:57:48.256 --> 00:57:51.343
Don't you want your daughter
to be an Israeli. Avner?

692
00:57:52.844 --> 00:57:54.930
She'll always be an Israeli.

693
00:57:55.389 --> 00:57:58.225
Not in Brooklyn.
She'll just be another homeless Jew.

694
00:57:58.350 --> 00:58:00.727
I can't do what I'm doing
if I can't see you.

695
00:58:00.852 --> 00:58:02.562
What are you doing?

696
00:58:04.398 --> 00:58:07.192
Don't do it then. Avner.
This is our home.

697
00:58:07.734 --> 00:58:10.070
You're the only home I ever had.

698
00:58:10.946 --> 00:58:12.072
What?

699
00:58:13.740 --> 00:58:15.367
This is so corny.

700
00:58:15.450 --> 00:58:17.869
- It wasn't easy for me to say that.
- I bet.

701
00:58:17.953 --> 00:58:20.080
Don't laugh at me then.

702
00:58:20.205 --> 00:58:22.916
Why did I have to marry
a sentimentalist?

703
00:58:23.041 --> 00:58:24.918
You're ruining my life.

704
00:58:25.293 --> 00:58:27.295
Your mother's teasing me.

705
00:58:40.642 --> 00:58:43.103
Look at the waistline bulge on that guy.

706
00:58:43.478 --> 00:58:46.106
Look at that.
Think he might be armed. eh?

707
00:58:46.606 --> 00:58:48.442
As are the Russians.

708
00:58:49.276 --> 00:58:50.986
It's definitely him.

709
00:58:51.445 --> 00:58:53.238
Hussein Abad al-Chir.

710
00:58:53.780 --> 00:58:56.283
His room is next to Israeli newlyweds.

711
00:58:56.950 --> 00:58:59.244
They married in Cyprus
because she's not Jewish.

712
00:58:59.327 --> 00:59:00.746
A mixed marriage.

713
00:59:00.829 --> 00:59:02.330
A shande for the goyim.

714
00:59:02.456 --> 00:59:05.125
Yeah. okay.
But let's try not to blow them up.

715
00:59:05.292 --> 00:59:08.045
The KGB brings him home
every night after dark.

716
00:59:08.128 --> 00:59:10.589
He turns on the light. gets undressed.

717
00:59:10.672 --> 00:59:14.134
turns off the light. gets into bed.
we blow up the bed.

718
00:59:15.802 --> 00:59:19.306
I knew a field agent who got
too scared to sleep in his bed.

719
00:59:19.431 --> 00:59:22.642
So every night he slept on the floor
of his closet.

720
00:59:23.643 --> 00:59:25.479
He still does. every night.

721
00:59:26.146 --> 00:59:27.606
Sleeps in closets.

722
00:59:27.689 --> 00:59:30.734
Now if al-Chir sleeps in his closet.
we're in trouble.

723
00:59:30.817 --> 00:59:34.362
But if he gets in the bed.
his weight arms the device.

724
00:59:34.988 --> 00:59:36.865
it closes the circuit.

725
00:59:37.824 --> 00:59:40.160
Then we hit the remote.

726
00:59:47.667 --> 00:59:48.835
Okay.

727
00:59:49.461 --> 00:59:51.838
Okay. we're good. We're good. let's go.

728
00:59:56.343 --> 00:59:57.719
Careful.

729
01:00:01.807 --> 01:00:04.351
I've checked into the room next door.

730
01:00:06.186 --> 01:00:08.230
- Why?
- There are balconies.

731
01:00:08.855 --> 01:00:10.482
When he gets into bed.

732
01:00:10.565 --> 01:00:13.527
I give the signal
by switching off the light.

733
01:00:14.194 --> 01:00:17.531
And if the bomb's too powerful
and you're in the next room?

734
01:00:18.031 --> 01:00:19.699
Well. that won't happen.

735
01:00:19.908 --> 01:00:21.159
Right?

736
01:00:21.660 --> 01:00:22.869
Robert?

737
01:00:23.495 --> 01:00:25.080
- Robert?
- Robert?

738
01:00:26.373 --> 01:00:27.874
It won't. No.

739
01:00:28.875 --> 01:00:30.001
Okay.

740
01:00:31.586 --> 01:00:32.754
Avner.

741
01:00:35.048 --> 01:00:36.424
Boy or girl?

742
01:00:37.843 --> 01:00:39.052
A girl.

743
01:00:40.262 --> 01:00:41.555
Mazel tov.

744
01:00:45.392 --> 01:00:47.060
News from Paris.

745
01:00:48.895 --> 01:00:51.731
Dr Hamshari succumbed to his wounds.

746
01:00:52.566 --> 01:00:56.236
So. again. mazel tov. Avner.

747
01:01:51.333 --> 01:01:52.959
Steve. shut up.

748
01:02:12.479 --> 01:02:13.521
Hey.

749
01:02:34.000 --> 01:02:35.335
Good evening.

750
01:02:36.503 --> 01:02:38.004
Good evening.

751
01:02:38.171 --> 01:02:39.631
Beautiful night.

752
01:02:39.714 --> 01:02:41.675
Beautiful night. yeah.

753
01:02:43.385 --> 01:02:46.263
- Where are you from? I can't place...
- Diisseldorf.

754
01:02:46.346 --> 01:02:48.682
Yes? I wouldn't have guessed it.

755
01:02:50.141 --> 01:02:52.185
I thought perhaps a Swede.

756
01:02:54.479 --> 01:02:57.357
I taught in Sweden.
Near Eastern languages.

757
01:02:57.857 --> 01:02:59.025
Really?

758
01:02:59.567 --> 01:03:02.612
Teaching Lebanese immigrant women
how to clean houses.

759
01:03:02.696 --> 01:03:04.155
In Swedish.

760
01:03:12.163 --> 01:03:14.082
Were you here last night?

761
01:03:14.541 --> 01:03:17.544
No. Just checked in. Just arrived.

762
01:03:19.004 --> 01:03:20.755
Don't plan to sleep.

763
01:03:21.381 --> 01:03:23.383
They keep at it all night.

764
01:03:24.009 --> 01:03:25.677
There. for hours.

765
01:03:26.845 --> 01:03:28.096
- Take a sleeping pill.
- That's okay.

766
01:03:28.221 --> 01:03:29.723
- I can sleep through anything.
- Are you sure?

767
01:03:29.848 --> 01:03:30.974
You don't want to borrow one of mine?

768
01:03:31.057 --> 01:03:32.726
- Thank you very much. It's okay.
- Really?

769
01:03:32.851 --> 01:03:33.893
Yes.

770
01:03:34.019 --> 01:03:35.854
So. good night.

771
01:03:36.688 --> 01:03:38.231
Pleasant dreams.

772
01:04:26.613 --> 01:04:28.114
Wait for the signal.

773
01:04:28.740 --> 01:04:30.909
Wait for Avner's light to go out.

774
01:05:30.844 --> 01:05:32.303
Go! Go! Go!

775
01:05:51.656 --> 01:05:53.366
- Oh. my God!
- Help!

776
01:05:54.826 --> 01:05:57.829
Oh. my eyes. My eyes. I can't see.

777
01:05:57.996 --> 01:05:59.873
Can someone help me?

778
01:05:59.998 --> 01:06:01.541
I can't see.

779
01:06:01.875 --> 01:06:03.001
Avner!

780
01:06:07.547 --> 01:06:09.174
Please! Oh. my God!

781
01:06:10.842 --> 01:06:12.218
I can't see.

782
01:06:13.928 --> 01:06:15.597
- Can you see?
- Yes.

783
01:06:15.722 --> 01:06:17.015
- The stairs are that way.
- Okay.

784
01:06:17.098 --> 01:06:19.350
- Go that way.
- Come on. Let's go!

785
01:06:21.519 --> 01:06:23.730
- It was much too powerful.
- Stop it.

786
01:06:23.855 --> 01:06:25.648
- You could've blown up innocent...
- Target number three.

787
01:06:25.732 --> 01:06:26.858
Target number three was not in doubt.

788
01:06:26.941 --> 01:06:29.277
The ceiling in the lobby cracked.
You nearly demolished...

789
01:06:29.402 --> 01:06:30.904
Avner might have been killed.

790
01:06:31.029 --> 01:06:32.489
The plastique was not what I asked for.

791
01:06:32.572 --> 01:06:34.282
It couldn't have been
the grade I specified.

792
01:06:34.407 --> 01:06:36.409
Someone changed the marking
on the explosive.

793
01:06:36.534 --> 01:06:38.411
What if someone changed the marking?

794
01:06:38.536 --> 01:06:40.497
- What do you mean?
- Louis provided the plastique.

795
01:06:40.580 --> 01:06:43.082
Avner. Louis provided the explosives?

796
01:06:43.208 --> 01:06:45.710
- Yes. Why?
- Why are we trusting him?

797
01:06:46.544 --> 01:06:48.588
We have no idea who he is.

798
01:06:48.880 --> 01:06:50.632
- He's finding our targets.
- Yes. but...

799
01:06:50.757 --> 01:06:52.926
But without him.
we'd be nowhere on this!

800
01:06:53.051 --> 01:06:56.387
The plastique was much more powerful
than what I asked for.

801
01:06:56.971 --> 01:06:59.933
Someone changed the label.
I could have killed you.

802
01:07:00.058 --> 01:07:02.352
For all we know.
Louis works for the PLO.

803
01:07:02.435 --> 01:07:04.812
They're using us to do
internal housecleaning.

804
01:07:04.938 --> 01:07:06.022
That's bullshit.

805
01:07:06.105 --> 01:07:08.441
Hey. whose fishing boat is this?

806
01:07:14.280 --> 01:07:15.949
Louis arranged it.

807
01:07:48.648 --> 01:07:50.858
There was nothing wrong
with the explosive.

808
01:07:50.984 --> 01:07:54.028
Bomb makers are nervous.
which is understandable.

809
01:07:54.153 --> 01:07:55.363
Fear makes them sloppy...

810
01:07:55.488 --> 01:07:57.198
There's nothing wrong
with my bomb maker.

811
01:07:57.323 --> 01:07:59.117
It's your explosives.

812
01:08:00.201 --> 01:08:02.662
We found three more names for you.

813
01:08:03.162 --> 01:08:05.540
- Three?
- Yes. three.

814
01:08:07.792 --> 01:08:10.128
- Thought you'd be pleased.
- [ am.

815
01:08:11.546 --> 01:08:12.630
Who?

816
01:08:13.381 --> 01:08:17.218
Kemal Adwan. Kamal Nasser.
and Abu Youssef.

817
01:08:18.177 --> 01:08:20.054
Adwan and Abu Youssef.

818
01:08:20.805 --> 01:08:22.557
- Where?
- Lebanon.

819
01:08:23.391 --> 01:08:25.059
They're in Beirut.

820
01:08:25.184 --> 01:08:27.353
Adwan. Nasser. Youssef.

821
01:08:28.062 --> 01:08:30.064
Serious characters. huh?

822
01:08:30.189 --> 01:08:31.816
Extremely serious.

823
01:08:32.400 --> 01:08:35.820
Smile. Mr Storsch.
It's a second Christmas.

824
01:08:38.031 --> 01:08:40.491
I'd like to pay you a little extra for this.

825
01:08:40.575 --> 01:08:42.243
These three names.

826
01:08:44.203 --> 01:08:45.663
$600.000.

827
01:08:48.541 --> 01:08:50.960
Monsieur Storsch. my group.

828
01:08:51.044 --> 01:08:52.629
we don't care much for governments.

829
01:08:52.712 --> 01:08:54.172
any governments.

830
01:08:54.255 --> 01:08:56.090
We don't work with or for them.

831
01:08:56.215 --> 01:08:58.593
That's an absolute condition
of my theory.

832
01:08:58.718 --> 01:09:00.261
You understand?

833
01:09:00.386 --> 01:09:03.306
If I learn that your sudden
generosity was an attempt

834
01:09:03.389 --> 01:09:06.768
to buy our acquiescence
in your sharing my information

835
01:09:06.893 --> 01:09:10.563
with. let us say. CIA or MI6 or Mossad...

836
01:09:10.688 --> 01:09:13.650
- I don't work for MI6 or CIA...
- You have no idea who you work for.

837
01:09:13.733 --> 01:09:15.276
Trust me. You don't.

838
01:09:16.110 --> 01:09:19.572
Lie to me and you will find me
abruptly unreachable

839
01:09:20.239 --> 01:09:21.616
and unhappy.

840
01:09:22.950 --> 01:09:26.037
- Let me buy you a drink.
- No. You save your money.

841
01:09:26.120 --> 01:09:28.623
At these prices. you're going to need it.

842
01:09:29.457 --> 01:09:31.793
It's obviously significant information.

843
01:09:31.918 --> 01:09:35.880
Abu Youssef is like number three
in the whole Palestinian network.

844
01:09:36.255 --> 01:09:37.840
It's like Arafat. Habash. and then him.

845
01:09:37.924 --> 01:09:39.884
- Of course he's significant.
- Thanks for the instruction

846
01:09:39.967 --> 01:09:41.803
- and enthusiasm.
- He's the brains of the fedayeen.

847
01:09:41.928 --> 01:09:44.138
- I know who he is.
- Next to Salameh.

848
01:09:44.263 --> 01:09:46.391
Abu Youssef is the worst guy
we're after. right?

849
01:09:46.474 --> 01:09:49.936
And Adwan. he plans all the actions
in the West Bank. right?

850
01:09:50.436 --> 01:09:52.814
We get the significance.
These are serious targets.

851
01:09:52.939 --> 01:09:54.482
- We want to go to Beirut.
- No.

852
01:09:54.607 --> 01:09:56.067
You keep away from the Arab countries.

853
01:09:56.150 --> 01:09:58.486
Mossad and the army will take care of it.

854
01:09:58.611 --> 01:10:00.530
What is this contraption?

855
01:10:00.613 --> 01:10:03.449
You can't send the army.
We won't allow it.

856
01:10:04.784 --> 01:10:06.494
You won't allow it?

857
01:10:06.619 --> 01:10:08.705
Our source doesn't know we're Mossad.

858
01:10:08.788 --> 01:10:10.164
You aren't Mossad.

859
01:10:10.289 --> 01:10:12.917
If commandos go to Beirut.
our source will cut us off.

860
01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:16.045
Why don't you and I go for a walk
and talk about this. alone?

861
01:10:16.129 --> 01:10:17.505
The food will get cold.

862
01:10:17.630 --> 01:10:19.632
- We have to go to Beirut.
- We're good at this.

863
01:10:19.757 --> 01:10:21.509
This is our information. this is our job.

864
01:10:21.634 --> 01:10:23.970
That's touching in a juvenile sort of way.

865
01:10:24.095 --> 01:10:25.596
Listen. You're doing reasonably well.

866
01:10:25.680 --> 01:10:27.390
- Reasonably?
- You're spending a lot of money.

867
01:10:27.473 --> 01:10:29.183
Well. we expected that.

868
01:10:31.310 --> 01:10:34.313
Lots of people in Mossad
don't know about you.

869
01:10:34.480 --> 01:10:35.940
No one knows.

870
01:10:36.023 --> 01:10:38.651
So everyone's asking.
"Who's killing the fedayeen?

871
01:10:38.776 --> 01:10:40.737
"Is it our guys? Why weren't we told?"

872
01:10:40.820 --> 01:10:42.989
Big egos. Lots of screaming.

873
01:10:44.991 --> 01:10:46.993
I can maybe include one or two of you.

874
01:10:47.118 --> 01:10:49.537
but excluding Mossad
or the army is impossible.

875
01:10:49.662 --> 01:10:50.955
Accept it.

876
01:10:51.122 --> 01:10:53.332
We will. but our source won't.

877
01:10:54.459 --> 01:10:56.169
Who is your source?

878
01:10:57.628 --> 01:10:58.671
It's time you told me.

879
01:10:58.796 --> 01:11:00.757
That. by the way. is not a request.
It's an order.

880
01:11:00.840 --> 01:11:02.842
You can't order him.
He doesn't work for you.

881
01:11:02.967 --> 01:11:05.470
Shut up. I pay you. You work for me.

882
01:11:05.553 --> 01:11:08.806
I work for a metal box in a bank
in Geneva. The box pays me.

883
01:11:08.890 --> 01:11:11.809
- You want to find it empty?
- I want you to let us do our work!

884
01:11:11.893 --> 01:11:13.895
What's the matter with you?

885
01:11:14.020 --> 01:11:16.731
With all of you?
Grow up and do it quick.

886
01:11:16.856 --> 01:11:19.358
This is not a game. a fucking game.

887
01:11:19.525 --> 01:11:22.195
Who has the source? Where are you
getting your information?

888
01:11:22.320 --> 01:11:24.363
Give me his goddamn number!

889
01:11:25.072 --> 01:11:27.241
I hope the old lady next door
enjoyed that.

890
01:11:27.366 --> 01:11:30.995
She's a little deaf but I doubt
she had any trouble hearing you.

891
01:11:33.039 --> 01:11:36.083
Give me the source
and we'll let you take part.

892
01:11:36.584 --> 01:11:38.336
Let us go to Beirut.

893
01:11:38.419 --> 01:11:42.423
After Beirut. we'll use our source
to find the remaining targets.

894
01:11:42.882 --> 01:11:44.550
Let us do our job.

895
01:12:28.219 --> 01:12:30.888
A lot of manpower to shoot three guys.

896
01:12:59.166 --> 01:13:01.127
- Ehud Barak.
- Daniel.

897
01:13:37.997 --> 01:13:39.123
Go!

898
01:14:16.035 --> 01:14:17.870
Where the fuck is he?

899
01:14:20.665 --> 01:14:21.749
Door!

900
01:14:29.882 --> 01:14:31.092
- Let's go!
- Go!

901
01:14:32.093 --> 01:14:33.219
Go! Go!

902
01:14:35.388 --> 01:14:36.430
Go!

903
01:15:13.801 --> 01:15:16.262
- It's him!
- Don't shoot! No!

904
01:15:34.613 --> 01:15:35.823
Fedayeen!

905
01:15:42.997 --> 01:15:44.123
Go!

906
01:16:49.021 --> 01:16:52.191
- My papa would like to meet you.
- Papa?

907
01:16:52.399 --> 01:16:55.361
My papa. He runs our little group.

908
01:16:55.694 --> 01:16:57.530
I thought you ran the group.

909
01:16:57.905 --> 01:17:00.032
Everybody works for someone.

910
01:17:01.700 --> 01:17:03.410
I wasn't in Beirut.

911
01:17:03.869 --> 01:17:05.830
Well. someone was there.

912
01:17:05.913 --> 01:17:09.375
The Israeli army. according
to every newspaper on Earth.

913
01:17:09.542 --> 01:17:11.168
But you stayed away

914
01:17:11.252 --> 01:17:14.547
after you paid so extravagantly
for the information.

915
01:17:14.713 --> 01:17:17.299
I don't like to keep my papa waiting.

916
01:17:17.383 --> 01:17:19.593
I need to tell my people where I'm going.

917
01:17:19.718 --> 01:17:21.512
You don't know where you're going.

918
01:17:21.595 --> 01:17:24.515
And you'll need to wear this.

919
01:17:26.183 --> 01:17:27.601
Forget it. Louis. That's just crazy.

920
01:17:27.726 --> 01:17:29.270
We're done here.

921
01:17:35.734 --> 01:17:36.902
Shit.

922
01:17:37.736 --> 01:17:38.779
Wait!

923
01:17:40.239 --> 01:17:41.282
Wait!

924
01:18:27.286 --> 01:18:28.621
We're here.

925
01:18:49.266 --> 01:18:50.476
Papa!

926
01:19:05.991 --> 01:19:07.368
He's over there.

927
01:19:20.547 --> 01:19:22.633
Louis says you're a cook.

928
01:19:22.800 --> 01:19:24.802
I know how to cook. yeah.

929
01:19:25.219 --> 01:19:26.679
You help me?

930
01:19:32.059 --> 01:19:33.727
Bring these there.

931
01:19:38.983 --> 01:19:43.237
No. no. Don't wash. No. no.
They will taste like boiled sponge.

932
01:19:43.529 --> 01:19:45.489
But then why put them in the sink?

933
01:19:45.572 --> 01:19:48.075
If the juices spurt out. it's a big mess.

934
01:19:48.200 --> 01:19:50.828
The whole kitchen will smell like piss.

935
01:19:52.705 --> 01:19:54.373
Peel off the fat.

936
01:19:57.876 --> 01:19:59.712
Let me see your hands.

937
01:20:02.715 --> 01:20:04.675
Too big for a good cook.

938
01:20:04.883 --> 01:20:07.303
That was my problem. too.
I had been a master.

939
01:20:07.386 --> 01:20:10.764
but I have thick. stupid.
butcher's hands just like yours.

940
01:20:10.889 --> 01:20:14.768
Well. we are tragic men.
Butcher's hands. gentle souls.

941
01:20:28.240 --> 01:20:30.784
These are going to be too sour to eat.

942
01:20:31.035 --> 01:20:34.371
Skin them and prick them.
boil them in sugar.

943
01:20:35.080 --> 01:20:38.417
A little torture.
and you'll see how nice they are.

944
01:20:39.418 --> 01:20:42.504
- You call me "Papa."
- I can't do that.

945
01:20:42.588 --> 01:20:44.715
- No?
- I have a papa already.

946
01:20:46.884 --> 01:20:48.761
You are devoted to him?

947
01:20:49.428 --> 01:20:51.680
Am I here because
of what happened in Beirut?

948
01:20:51.764 --> 01:20:54.266
Your papa must be proud of his son.

949
01:20:55.809 --> 01:20:58.645
We'll pick a few. Let the rest ripen.

950
01:20:59.438 --> 01:21:01.231
There are so many people to feed. but...

951
01:21:01.315 --> 01:21:03.233
But they are your family.
So you have to feed them.

952
01:21:03.317 --> 01:21:06.403
Yes. We don't work with governments.

953
01:21:06.820 --> 01:21:08.447
Louis said. But...

954
01:21:08.572 --> 01:21:12.493
But you did what you did because
you have to feed your family.

955
01:21:31.678 --> 01:21:33.555
I blew up trains. bridges.

956
01:21:33.639 --> 01:21:36.475
and trucks full of Germans
during the war.

957
01:21:38.143 --> 01:21:42.815
My brothers were killed. my papa
and my sister were both hanged.

958
01:21:43.857 --> 01:21:45.109
She was a young girl.

959
01:21:45.192 --> 01:21:48.654
Papa. the guest doesn't want to hear
your war stories.

960
01:21:49.363 --> 01:21:53.075
We paid this price. so Vichy scum
could be replaced.

961
01:21:53.158 --> 01:21:54.993
by Gaullist scum.

962
01:21:55.119 --> 01:21:58.622
and the Nazis could be replaced
by Stalin and America.

963
01:21:59.289 --> 01:22:01.208
We stay away from governments.

964
01:22:02.626 --> 01:22:04.044
We say grace?

965
01:22:04.545 --> 01:22:06.839
Maybe our guest could lead us.

966
01:22:11.218 --> 01:22:13.220
No. no. no. It's not required.

967
01:22:16.974 --> 01:22:18.684
You lead us instead.

968
01:22:21.228 --> 01:22:24.982
Our Father. who gives us
obedient and respectful clients.

969
01:22:25.190 --> 01:22:27.693
who obey the rules according
to which our business thrives...

970
01:22:27.818 --> 01:22:30.696
I won't have my grandchildren
listen to this blasphemous...

971
01:22:30.779 --> 01:22:32.823
...whose prevarications
and deceptions...

972
01:22:32.906 --> 01:22:37.161
It's not all for business!
I didn't do all this for the fucking money!

973
01:22:38.537 --> 01:22:39.830
Why'd you do it then?

974
01:22:40.914 --> 01:22:42.583
You've made millions from this.

975
01:22:43.876 --> 01:22:46.545
In my despair I fathered madmen.

976
01:22:47.504 --> 01:22:51.550
who dress like factory workers.
but never do manual labour

977
01:22:51.717 --> 01:22:54.761
and who read nonsense
and spout pompous bullshit

978
01:22:54.887 --> 01:22:58.223
about Algerians and who love nothing

979
01:22:58.348 --> 01:22:59.766
not Algerians or French

980
01:22:59.892 --> 01:23:02.561
or flesh and blood. or anything living.

981
01:23:03.437 --> 01:23:07.232
So I have sympathy for a man
who can say. "I have a papa"

982
01:23:07.566 --> 01:23:10.277
and who does what he must
for his family.

983
01:23:10.527 --> 01:23:14.531
I did it for my family. for you.
You... centaur! You minotaur!

984
01:23:16.074 --> 01:23:17.743
I will say grace.

985
01:23:26.877 --> 01:23:28.837
There's some opinion
you should be punished

986
01:23:28.921 --> 01:23:31.089
for what happened in Beirut.

987
01:23:31.423 --> 01:23:33.383
We didn't know so many would die.

988
01:23:33.467 --> 01:23:36.929
I'm in business with death.
Do you think I'm squeamish?

989
01:23:39.473 --> 01:23:42.768
The world has been rough with you.
with your tribe.

990
01:23:45.062 --> 01:23:48.106
It's right to respond roughly
to such treatment.

991
01:23:49.775 --> 01:23:53.946
You pay well and you pay promptly.
so we'll continue together.

992
01:23:55.155 --> 01:23:58.909
- But no more infractions.
- Thank you. You have my word.

993
01:24:13.799 --> 01:24:17.803
A few andouillettes and boudins noirs

994
01:24:18.971 --> 01:24:23.183
black blood sausage and
a Loire cheese. Selles-sur-Cher.

995
01:24:24.017 --> 01:24:27.145
- We cover it in ash to preserve it.
- Thank you.

996
01:24:28.647 --> 01:24:30.774
You could have been my son.

997
01:24:33.527 --> 01:24:36.530
But you're not. Remember that.

998
01:24:37.990 --> 01:24:41.994
We'll do business. but you aren't family.

999
01:25:30.751 --> 01:25:32.836
I have a new name for you.

1000
01:25:34.046 --> 01:25:36.048
I want Ali Hassan Salameh.

1001
01:25:38.884 --> 01:25:39.926
No.

1002
01:25:41.094 --> 01:25:43.388
You know where he is.
You know where all the names are.

1003
01:25:43.513 --> 01:25:46.099
- Salameh.
- Untouchable.

1004
01:25:48.393 --> 01:25:49.728
Salameh.

1005
01:25:57.736 --> 01:25:59.237
Zaid Muchassi.

1006
01:26:03.033 --> 01:26:05.744
Zaid Muchassi is in Athens
in two weeks.

1007
01:26:06.286 --> 01:26:08.872
- Not one of our names.
- Nevertheless.

1008
01:26:09.081 --> 01:26:11.583
He is Black September's KGB contact.

1009
01:26:11.792 --> 01:26:14.211
Hussein al-Chir was the KGB contact.

1010
01:26:14.294 --> 01:26:17.673
Yes. But you put a bomb under
Monsieur al-Chir's bed in Cyprus

1011
01:26:17.756 --> 01:26:20.926
and now he's defunct.
Muchassi is his replacement.

1012
01:26:21.426 --> 01:26:24.429
I hear he's much tougher
than his predecessor.

1013
01:26:30.310 --> 01:26:33.772
We offer Muchassi's whereabouts
at the new rate.

1014
01:26:34.106 --> 01:26:37.567
- What new rate?
- Three names for $600.000

1015
01:26:37.651 --> 01:26:40.153
is $200.000 for one name.

1016
01:26:44.825 --> 01:26:47.953
I need you to find me
a place to work in Athens.

1017
01:26:48.245 --> 01:26:51.123
Of course. Safe house.

1018
01:27:13.979 --> 01:27:16.273
Is this Louis's idea of a joke?

1019
01:27:16.982 --> 01:27:19.776
I've had nightmares that looked like this.

1020
01:27:21.653 --> 01:27:24.531
So when they explode. they toss
little white balls of phosphorus

1021
01:27:24.656 --> 01:27:27.951
here all around his room.
Each ball. it's like a little sun.

1022
01:27:28.034 --> 01:27:29.995
It burns at around 5.000 degrees.

1023
01:27:30.120 --> 01:27:32.956
So the air catches fire.

1024
01:27:33.331 --> 01:27:35.751
Everything in the vicinity melts.

1025
01:27:35.834 --> 01:27:37.753
Now. the bad news is
they are grenades.

1026
01:27:37.836 --> 01:27:41.006
so I modified them
to use with a remote detonator.

1027
01:27:41.339 --> 01:27:43.300
I also should mention that
they're quite old.

1028
01:27:43.383 --> 01:27:44.760
like World War II.

1029
01:27:44.843 --> 01:27:47.888
Only four were viable.
We should dump the rest.

1030
01:27:48.972 --> 01:27:51.683
There's a porter at the hotel
where Muchassi's staying.

1031
01:27:51.808 --> 01:27:53.935
He's gonna let us in the room
when Muchassi goes out.

1032
01:27:54.019 --> 01:27:57.063
Hey. Who provided
these prehistoric explosives?

1033
01:27:57.189 --> 01:28:00.233
