1239
01:47:32.988 --> 01:47:34.531
Fucking Americans!

1240
01:47:34.657 --> 01:47:36.367
- What the fuck is that?
- Was it Salameh?

1241
01:47:36.492 --> 01:47:38.827
Yes. of course it was fucking Salameh!

1242
01:48:00.432 --> 01:48:03.018
I take it she'd eat you up a bit. huh?

1243
01:48:04.353 --> 01:48:05.938
You old dog.

1244
01:48:06.230 --> 01:48:08.023
He's got some ideas.

1245
01:48:09.358 --> 01:48:11.860
- Oh. the American bloke?
- Aren't we all?

1246
01:48:12.277 --> 01:48:14.989
So you've heard these rumours?
These are wild stories.

1247
01:48:15.072 --> 01:48:17.032
- Wild stories.
- Yeah?

1248
01:48:17.116 --> 01:48:18.242
Yeah.

1249
01:48:43.142 --> 01:48:44.309
Can I?

1250
01:48:52.443 --> 01:48:56.780
I have to go to bed soon.
I work in the morning.

1251
01:48:57.781 --> 01:48:59.908
What kind of work do you do?

1252
01:49:02.578 --> 01:49:04.997
The kind that drives you to drink.

1253
01:49:05.789 --> 01:49:07.833
We must have the same job. then.

1254
01:49:09.460 --> 01:49:11.253
I love your accent.

1255
01:49:12.254 --> 01:49:13.797
I love your perfume.

1256
01:49:24.308 --> 01:49:26.477
Cuts right through the smoke.

1257
01:49:28.479 --> 01:49:29.688
Does it?

1258
01:49:30.856 --> 01:49:32.649
It's very nice.

1259
01:49:37.488 --> 01:49:40.657
Look. I don't want to be forward.

1260
01:49:41.366 --> 01:49:42.993
but it's late

1261
01:49:43.452 --> 01:49:46.789
and I do have to get up early.

1262
01:49:47.456 --> 01:49:48.624
So...

1263
01:49:50.292 --> 01:49:52.669
- So0?
- So...

1264
01:49:54.296 --> 01:49:56.507
So. you're very nice. and...

1265
01:50:00.010 --> 01:50:02.513
Are you really going to make me ask?

1266
01:50:09.394 --> 01:50:10.687
I just can't.

1267
01:50:12.022 --> 01:50:13.148
Pity.

1268
01:50:13.857 --> 01:50:16.527
- You're very attractive.
- I know.

1269
01:50:19.696 --> 01:50:21.281
If you come to your senses

1270
01:50:21.365 --> 01:50:23.992
once you get up to your lonely room.

1271
01:50:24.201 --> 01:50:26.203
well. maybe I'll be here.

1272
01:50:27.162 --> 01:50:31.500
Or maybe I'll be in my room.
alone in bed.

1273
01:50:38.382 --> 01:50:39.758
Good night.

1274
01:50:59.361 --> 01:51:02.614
The drunk Americans.
You think they were CIA?

1275
01:51:03.407 --> 01:51:06.785
They could've been.
For all we know. Louis is CIA.

1276
01:51:06.910 --> 01:51:09.496
They work both sides. Everyone does.

1277
01:51:09.580 --> 01:51:12.541
Or Louis is Mossad.
Now. maybe he isn't.

1278
01:51:12.624 --> 01:51:14.293
but they're using him
to feed us information.

1279
01:51:14.418 --> 01:51:15.961
There's no direct link.

1280
01:51:16.086 --> 01:51:18.881
Or Mossad's giving it to CIA.
which is giving it to Louis

1281
01:51:18.964 --> 01:51:20.799
and Ephraim's demanding
we give him Louis

1282
01:51:20.924 --> 01:51:23.343
because he knows
we expect him to do...

1283
01:51:23.427 --> 01:51:26.388
Stop chasing the mice inside your skull.

1284
01:51:31.435 --> 01:51:34.396
You know. I never thought you'd last.

1285
01:51:35.606 --> 01:51:37.566
I thought the same about you.

1286
01:51:37.649 --> 01:51:40.360
From the beginning
you seemed so reluctant.

1287
01:51:40.444 --> 01:51:42.321
I was born reluctant. Ask my mother.

1288
01:51:42.446 --> 01:51:44.031
If I can't kvetch. I can't do my job.

1289
01:51:44.114 --> 01:51:46.116
You ever feel reluctant?

1290
01:51:46.450 --> 01:51:48.744
I'm not comfortable with confusion.

1291
01:51:49.995 --> 01:51:52.414
I knew guys like you in the army.

1292
01:51:52.789 --> 01:51:55.334
You'll do any terrifying thing
you're asked to do.

1293
01:51:55.459 --> 01:51:57.628
but you have to do it running.

1294
01:51:58.754 --> 01:52:02.966
You think you can outrun your fears.
your doubts.

1295
01:52:04.843 --> 01:52:09.681
The only thing that really scares
you guys is stillness.

1296
01:52:11.642 --> 01:52:14.603
But everyone's overtaken. eventually.

1297
01:52:16.313 --> 01:52:18.899
Now. the mice need a brandy.
Will you join me?

1298
01:52:18.982 --> 01:52:21.568
No. I'm going to go upstairs.
straight to bed.

1299
01:52:21.652 --> 01:52:22.903
You okay drinking by yourself?

1300
01:52:22.986 --> 01:52:25.781
It's just a shot to numb the brain.
Good night.

1301
01:52:30.953 --> 01:52:33.830
- Beware of the local honey trap.
- Indeed?

1302
01:52:34.790 --> 01:52:37.501
You can't miss her. You don't want to.

1303
01:52:58.188 --> 01:52:59.356
Hello.

1304
01:52:59.481 --> 01:53:01.650
This is a trunk call from Mr Storsch.

1305
01:53:01.733 --> 01:53:02.985
Do you accept the charges?

1306
01:53:03.068 --> 01:53:06.238
Shit. Avner. you woke up the baby.
but that's okay... I mean...

1307
01:53:06.363 --> 01:53:07.698
How are you?

1308
01:53:08.865 --> 01:53:09.992
1 miss you.

1309
01:53:10.826 --> 01:53:13.954
You're in England or Australia

1310
01:53:14.037 --> 01:53:16.540
- or the North Pole...
- Yeah. that's right.

1311
01:53:18.500 --> 01:53:20.627
So listen. I was thinking

1312
01:53:20.711 --> 01:53:23.547
when I'm finished doing
what I'm doing here.

1313
01:53:23.672 --> 01:53:25.299
I want to come to Brooklyn to see you.

1314
01:53:25.382 --> 01:53:28.135
Brooklyn is depressing. It's got
more churches than Jerusalem.

1315
01:53:28.218 --> 01:53:30.012
Listen to her talk.

1316
01:53:32.055 --> 01:53:35.183
- Can you hear me? Can she hear me?
- Yeah. yeah.

1317
01:53:36.101 --> 01:53:39.354
Hey. Talk to me.

1318
01:53:41.940 --> 01:53:44.401
Daphna. make her talk.

1319
01:53:54.911 --> 01:53:55.954
Dada.

1320
01:54:00.876 --> 01:54:03.920
Hey. Hey. sweetheart. It's your papa.

1321
01:54:06.089 --> 01:54:08.091
This is my voice. darling.

1322
01:54:10.427 --> 01:54:13.430
This is what I sound like.
Don't forget. okay?

1323
01:54:15.640 --> 01:54:18.518
Listen. I have to get her to bed.
She's tired.

1324
01:54:18.602 --> 01:54:20.562
She'll dream about you.

1325
01:54:53.095 --> 01:54:56.181
We re standing at a distance.
as instructed by the terrorists.

1326
01:54:58.100 --> 01:55:00.602
Are we going? Is it to the airport?

1327
01:55:00.685 --> 01:55:01.937
Can we talk to someone. just to say...

1328
01:55:02.020 --> 01:55:03.980
Shut up. okay?
Just get on the bus. okay?

1329
01:55:04.106 --> 01:55:07.651
Just to tell our families.
Just to say we are all right!

1330
01:55:07.776 --> 01:55:10.529
Everybody. just relax. okay? Relax!
Calm down.

1331
01:55:10.654 --> 01:55:14.699
We will ride this bus and fly away.
After. you go back to your home

1332
01:55:14.825 --> 01:55:16.827
or to your Olympic Games.

1333
01:57:14.819 --> 01:57:17.656
Carl. You asshole.

1334
01:57:18.448 --> 01:57:20.116
I saw her first.

1335
01:57:38.468 --> 01:57:39.636
Carl?

1336
01:59:17.108 --> 01:59:20.445
She's Dutch. not political.
entirely business-minded.

1337
01:59:21.029 --> 01:59:23.573
She lives in Hoorn. She's there now.

1338
01:59:24.115 --> 01:59:26.159
This is dependable information.

1339
01:59:26.242 --> 01:59:28.286
For which you pay nothing.

1340
01:59:28.578 --> 01:59:31.206
We're giving you this.
You understand why?

1341
01:59:31.289 --> 01:59:33.541
Because you want me to believe
that you had nothing to do

1342
01:59:33.625 --> 01:59:35.460
with the murder of my partner.

1343
01:59:35.585 --> 01:59:39.089
We inhabit a world
of intersecting secrecies.

1344
01:59:39.464 --> 01:59:42.967
We live and die at the places
where those secrecies meet.

1345
01:59:43.093 --> 01:59:44.969
That's what we accept.

1346
01:59:45.804 --> 01:59:48.765
We buy information for you
from your enemies.

1347
01:59:50.266 --> 01:59:51.393
This alerts them.

1348
01:59:51.476 --> 01:59:54.145
You're not the only people
looking for names.

1349
01:59:54.771 --> 01:59:56.773
You're telling me I'm being hunted now?

1350
01:59:56.898 --> 01:59:59.734
He's telling you it's time for you to quit.

1351
01:59:59.818 --> 02:00:03.613
The race is not to the swift.
nor the battle to the strong

1352
02:00:03.738 --> 02:00:06.449
but time and chance
happens to them all.

1353
02:00:19.129 --> 02:00:20.839
Evil falls suddenly.

1354
02:00:23.174 --> 02:00:25.176
Who can say when it falls?

1355
02:00:48.616 --> 02:00:50.952
So you're really gonna kill her?

1356
02:00:52.287 --> 02:00:56.332
- All this blood comes back to us.
- Eventually it will work.

1357
02:00:56.791 --> 02:00:59.502
Even if it takes years. we'll beat them.

1358
02:01:00.503 --> 02:01:02.172
We're Jews. Avner.

1359
02:01:02.714 --> 02:01:04.841
Jews don't do wrong
because our enemies do wrong.

1360
02:01:04.966 --> 02:01:07.385
We can't afford to be
that decent any more.

1361
02:01:07.510 --> 02:01:09.971
[ don't know that we ever were
that decent.

1362
02:01:10.054 --> 02:01:13.975
Suffering thousands of years
of hatred doesn't make you decent.

1363
02:01:14.225 --> 02:01:17.896
But we're supposed to be righteous.
That's a beautiful thing.

1364
02:01:18.021 --> 02:01:19.355
That's Jewish.

1365
02:01:19.481 --> 02:01:22.150
That's what I knew.
that's what I was taught.

1366
02:01:22.817 --> 02:01:25.570
And now I'm losing it.
and I lose that. that's...

1367
02:01:25.695 --> 02:01:27.822
- That's...
- That's everything.

1368
02:01:28.490 --> 02:01:30.033
That's my soul.

1369
02:01:32.994 --> 02:01:36.498
You need to go rest somewhere.
You don't have to do this one.

1370
02:01:38.374 --> 02:01:40.668
When I need you again. I'll find you.

1371
02:02:33.721 --> 02:02:35.890
Excuse me. Who are you?

1372
02:02:44.148 --> 02:02:45.984
Do you know why we're here?

1373
02:02:46.401 --> 02:02:48.278
I want to get dressed. okay?

1374
02:02:54.325 --> 02:02:57.579
Maybe you want to hire me.
You know how good I am.

1375
02:03:02.834 --> 02:03:04.002
No. Don't.

1376
02:03:04.836 --> 02:03:07.338
It's such a fucking waste of talent.

1377
02:03:18.975 --> 02:03:20.810
Where're you going? Stay here.

1378
02:03:20.935 --> 02:03:22.353
Shell. Shell.

1379
02:03:23.271 --> 02:03:24.355
Yeah.

1380
02:04:00.308 --> 02:04:01.559
Leave it.

1381
02:04:19.827 --> 02:04:22.997
In seven months
we've killed six of the 11 names.

1382
02:04:23.748 --> 02:04:26.042
We've killed one replacement.

1383
02:04:26.376 --> 02:04:28.419
One of our targets is in prison and four.

1384
02:04:28.544 --> 02:04:31.381
including Ali Hassan Salameh.
are at large.

1385
02:04:32.256 --> 02:04:34.258
One of our own has fallen.

1386
02:04:35.093 --> 02:04:38.096
Since we began. the other side has
sent letter bombs to 11 embassies.

1387
02:04:38.221 --> 02:04:40.181
hijacked three planes.

1388
02:04:40.682 --> 02:04:44.268
killed 130 passengers in Athens
and wounded scores more.

1389
02:04:44.936 --> 02:04:47.563
and Killed our military attaché
in Washington.

1390
02:04:47.689 --> 02:04:51.109
Some of it was done by a Venezuelan
called Carlos the Jackal

1391
02:04:51.234 --> 02:04:53.069
who replaced Zaid Muchassi

1392
02:04:53.194 --> 02:04:55.405
who replaced Hussein al-Chir.

1393
02:04:56.531 --> 02:05:00.076
Black September's original
leadership has been decimated.

1394
02:05:02.120 --> 02:05:04.455
But new leaders are emerging

1395
02:05:04.747 --> 02:05:07.458
for whom Black September
wasn't violent enough.

1396
02:05:10.294 --> 02:05:12.922
And to dispatch our six
dispatched targets.

1397
02:05:13.047 --> 02:05:16.300
we must have spent something
close to $2 million. right?

1398
02:05:16.426 --> 02:05:19.721
You've been cooking.
Are you expecting company?

1399
02:05:20.596 --> 02:05:22.932
Mrs Meir says to the Knesset

1400
02:05:24.767 --> 02:05:27.395
the world must see that killing Jews

1401
02:05:27.603 --> 02:05:30.481
will be from now on
an expensive proposition.

1402
02:05:32.775 --> 02:05:35.445
But killing Palestinians
isn't exactly cheap.

1403
02:05:38.656 --> 02:05:42.285
- If all 11 were dead. you'd stop?
- Yes.

1404
02:05:43.578 --> 02:05:47.665
You're lying.
What about their replacements?

1405
02:05:48.416 --> 02:05:51.252
With each time we Kill.
we create six more.

1406
02:05:52.170 --> 02:05:53.963
Maybe they'll have to keep
killing them. then.

1407
02:05:54.088 --> 02:05:55.298
Forever.

1408
02:05:56.466 --> 02:05:58.551
Five targets are still alive.

1409
02:05:58.634 --> 02:06:00.636
That's five men that need to be killed.

1410
02:06:00.762 --> 02:06:03.264
Eventually you forget that
in the beginning you hated doing it.

1411
02:06:03.347 --> 02:06:04.932
For me personally. I feel less every day.

1412
02:06:05.016 --> 02:06:07.018
One day I'm going to wake up.
I'm going to kill.

1413
02:06:07.143 --> 02:06:10.938
I'm going to go back to bed. I'm not
going to feel anything at all.

1414
02:06:12.190 --> 02:06:16.360
Hey. Hans? You know there's a rule
in the book against blind drunks.

1415
02:06:16.652 --> 02:06:18.529
Why don't you stop drinking
and eat something?

1416
02:06:18.654 --> 02:06:21.866
I mean. there's enough food here
to feed Bangladesh.

1417
02:06:24.869 --> 02:06:28.539
I keep seeing that Dutch woman.
you know. sprawled out like that.

1418
02:06:32.043 --> 02:06:34.962
It's not that I wish we hadn't killed her.

1419
02:06:35.213 --> 02:06:38.049
I wish I had let you close up
her housecoat.

1420
02:06:38.633 --> 02:06:42.178
Yeah. but you weren't yourself.

1421
02:06:57.068 --> 02:06:58.236
Avner.

1422
02:07:06.327 --> 02:07:09.330
I went to Hans' flat
above the antique shop

1423
02:07:09.872 --> 02:07:12.834
just to check up on him
because he was so...

1424
02:07:13.835 --> 02:07:16.671
Anyway. he's gone somewhere.
and I waited all night

1425
02:07:16.754 --> 02:07:18.506
and he's not come back.

1426
02:07:39.527 --> 02:07:40.695
Knife.

1427
02:07:45.783 --> 02:07:47.785
They didn't take anything.

1428
02:12:09.964 --> 02:12:11.006
What?

1429
02:12:41.996 --> 02:12:43.747
It will be beautiful.

1430
02:12:45.207 --> 02:12:48.711
Ali Hassan Salameh is in Tarifa
on the Spanish coast.

1431
02:12:49.753 --> 02:12:53.382
He's at a compound guarded
by all the predictable trouble.

1432
02:12:53.757 --> 02:12:56.510
Bomb makers often die
accidental deaths.

1433
02:12:58.888 --> 02:13:01.223
In Athens you shot a KGB agent.

1434
02:13:03.350 --> 02:13:06.604
Many people must want to kill you.
Monsieur Storsch.

1435
02:13:07.021 --> 02:13:10.357
But why would I do that?
You pay better than anyone.

1436
02:13:15.863 --> 02:13:18.365
It's dangerous going after Salameh.

1437
02:13:19.700 --> 02:13:21.911
But he planned the Munich massacre.

1438
02:13:25.706 --> 02:13:29.418
Eliminate him. and they'll let you
go home. Don't you think?

1439
02:13:32.922 --> 02:13:34.548
Yes. Louis. I do.

1440
02:13:38.594 --> 02:13:41.430
You could have a kitchen
like that someday.

1441
02:13:44.558 --> 02:13:48.312
It costs dearly. but home always does.

1442
02:14:44.994 --> 02:14:47.496
Shit! It's like a funhouse in there.

1443
02:14:48.330 --> 02:14:50.165
Can you tell how many?

1444
02:15:10.019 --> 02:15:11.353
That's him.

1445
02:15:15.858 --> 02:15:18.068
Are you sure it's him. Avner?

1446
02:15:19.737 --> 02:15:21.530
You have to be sure.

1447
02:16:23.759 --> 02:16:25.386
- I'm Avner Kaufman.
- We know.

1448
02:16:25.469 --> 02:16:27.930
- You want to ride with us?
- Hop in.

1449
02:16:28.263 --> 02:16:29.598
Please.

1450
02:16:35.437 --> 02:16:38.440
I'm Amos. This is Avi. Shin Bet.

1451
02:16:39.400 --> 02:16:41.902
We're not supposed to know
who you are

1452
02:16:42.152 --> 02:16:43.362
because we're not officers.

1453
02:16:43.445 --> 02:16:46.240
We're just shit and no one tells us shit.

1454
02:16:47.991 --> 02:16:50.619
We've heard about what you've done.

1455
02:16:52.621 --> 02:16:55.124
We want to say
it's an honour to meet you.

1456
02:17:00.129 --> 02:17:02.172
It's an honour for me. too.

1457
02:17:11.640 --> 02:17:13.934
I have no problems
with anything you guys did

1458
02:17:14.017 --> 02:17:16.854
except the woman on the houseboat
in Hoorn.

1459
02:17:17.479 --> 02:17:19.231
Steve's told us about her.

1460
02:17:19.314 --> 02:17:20.482
We took a leave of absence

1461
02:17:20.607 --> 02:17:21.900
and Killed her off the company clock.

1462
02:17:21.984 --> 02:17:23.068
Don't be an idiot.

1463
02:17:23.152 --> 02:17:26.780
Otherwise. as I said. we have
no problems with the job you did.

1464
02:17:27.156 --> 02:17:29.241
Except three of my men died.

1465
02:17:29.324 --> 02:17:30.409
According to your colleague.

1466
02:17:30.492 --> 02:17:32.619
I should say. emphatically.
according to your colleague.

1467
02:17:32.703 --> 02:17:34.246
not in any way your fault.

1468
02:17:34.329 --> 02:17:35.456
He sings your praises.

1469
02:17:35.539 --> 02:17:38.167
Best guy he ever worked for. and so on.

1470
02:17:42.004 --> 02:17:45.174
He says this French group...
Louis was his name?

1471
02:17:45.507 --> 02:17:48.469
They sold the terrorists information
regarding your whereabouts.

1472
02:17:48.552 --> 02:17:50.345
They helped kill your men.

1473
02:17:51.555 --> 02:17:53.807
I know Steve believes that.
but it's not true.

1474
02:17:53.891 --> 02:17:55.517
Tell us who they are.

1475
02:17:57.853 --> 02:17:59.855
They won't work with you.

1476
02:18:01.231 --> 02:18:04.359
- It's about loyalty.
- You're an Israeli officer.

1477
02:18:04.526 --> 02:18:07.070
That's your only loyalty! That's it!

1478
02:18:09.990 --> 02:18:11.033
Okay.

1479
02:18:12.701 --> 02:18:15.662
This is General Hofi
of the Northern Command.

1480
02:18:15.829 --> 02:18:17.331
You look good.

1481
02:18:18.040 --> 02:18:21.543
Listen. the Prime Minister is proud
of you and your men.

1482
02:18:21.710 --> 02:18:23.712
She wishes she could tell you
herself. but she can't.

1483
02:18:23.837 --> 02:18:25.839
She never heard of you. right?

1484
02:18:26.548 --> 02:18:30.010
Good. She says you've done
a great thing for your people.

1485
02:18:30.093 --> 02:18:31.428
For Israel.

1486
02:18:35.891 --> 02:18:38.727
That's it. There is no medal or anything.

1487
02:18:50.405 --> 02:18:53.408
June 16. 1973.
Avner Kaufman interview.

1488
02:18:55.911 --> 02:18:57.204
Go ahead.

1489
02:19:01.583 --> 02:19:03.585
Tell me what you learnt.

1490
02:19:06.547 --> 02:19:08.423
- What I learnt?
- Yes.

1491
02:19:08.632 --> 02:19:10.425
What did you learn?

1492
02:19:13.053 --> 02:19:14.429
For God's sake!

1493
02:19:14.596 --> 02:19:17.307
Tell me the names and numbers
of your sources.

1494
02:19:21.395 --> 02:19:22.855
Avner. tell me.

1495
02:19:22.938 --> 02:19:25.941
Tell me the names and numbers
of your sources.

1496
02:19:27.317 --> 02:19:28.569
Please.

1497
02:19:29.778 --> 02:19:32.739
I can have you court-martialled.
and I might.

1498
02:19:33.448 --> 02:19:36.618
You can't. I don't work for you.

1499
02:19:38.495 --> 02:19:39.997
I don't exist.

1500
02:19:42.332 --> 02:19:45.294
- You look terrible.
- I'm not good right now.

1501
02:19:47.796 --> 02:19:51.633
You don't need to tell me anything.
It's taken a lot from you.

1502
02:19:52.342 --> 02:19:56.430
I'm alive. right?
And the rest sorts itself out.

1503
02:19:57.931 --> 02:20:01.310
- I'm not a fool. Avner.
- I never said you were a fool.

1504
02:20:11.445 --> 02:20:15.198
Everyone in Europe died.
Most of my family.

1505
02:20:16.158 --> 02:20:17.659
A huge family.

1506
02:20:21.330 --> 02:20:23.665
I never talked to you about it.

1507
02:20:23.832 --> 02:20:26.835
- I knew.
- You knew? So what was there to say?

1508
02:20:28.295 --> 02:20:30.672
I didn't die. because I came here.

1509
02:20:31.006 --> 02:20:34.426
When I arrived. I walked up
to the top of a hill in Jerusalem

1510
02:20:34.509 --> 02:20:37.471
and prayed for a child.

1511
02:20:37.679 --> 02:20:40.682
I never prayed before.
but I was praying then.

1512
02:20:40.807 --> 02:20:44.019
And I could feel every one of them
praying with me.

1513
02:20:47.564 --> 02:20:49.691
You are what we prayed for.

1514
02:20:50.859 --> 02:20:53.028
What you did. you did for us.

1515
02:20:53.487 --> 02:20:56.323
You did for your daughter.
but also for us.

1516
02:20:56.698 --> 02:20:59.868
Every one of the ones who died.
died wanting this.

1517
02:21:01.536 --> 02:21:05.207
We had to take it. because no one
will ever give it to us.

1518
02:21:05.332 --> 02:21:08.543
A place to be a Jew among Jews.
subject to no one.

1519
02:21:10.712 --> 02:21:13.090
I thank God for hearing my prayer.

1520
02:21:15.258 --> 02:21:17.344
Do you want to know. Mama?

1521
02:21:18.887 --> 02:21:21.390
Do you want me to tell you what I did?

1522
02:21:23.392 --> 02:21:24.518
No.

1523
02:21:25.894 --> 02:21:29.398
Whatever it took. whatever it takes.

1524
02:21:31.233 --> 02:21:36.238
A place on Earth.
We have a place on Earth.

1525
02:21:37.698 --> 02:21:38.907
At last.

1526
02:21:48.792 --> 02:21:50.919
- What's this?
- Baklava.

1527
02:21:51.753 --> 02:21:54.965
From Rehovot? The only edible
baklava is from the Arabs in Jaffa.

1528
02:21:55.090 --> 02:21:57.259
Eat it on the plane. You're too thin.

1529
02:21:57.384 --> 02:21:59.428
I hope it gives you a bellyache.

1530
02:22:00.804 --> 02:22:02.180
Listen. forget it.

1531
02:22:02.264 --> 02:22:04.933
You go see your wife. your child.
rest for a few more months.

1532
02:22:05.058 --> 02:22:06.768
Then we're gonna
put you back in the field.

1533
02:22:06.893 --> 02:22:08.603
Not Europe. Probably Latin America.

1534
02:22:08.729 --> 02:22:11.898
You think it over. Rest. Avner.
Then you come back.

1535
02:22:14.109 --> 02:22:15.235
No.

1536
02:22:42.137 --> 02:22:43.221
That's all right.

1537
02:22:43.305 --> 02:22:46.767
Oh. no. no. no. It's okay. It's okay.

1538
02:22:46.850 --> 02:22:50.020
Look at that beautiful hair.

1539
02:23:37.025 --> 02:23:38.360
Nightmares?

1540
02:23:39.528 --> 02:23:40.570
Yes.

1541
02:23:44.032 --> 02:23:45.659
Come back to bed.

1542
02:23:48.203 --> 02:23:50.539
I have no idea where I should be.

1543
02:23:56.920 --> 02:24:01.383
The place is nice.
You've made it really nice.

1544
02:24:02.717 --> 02:24:04.553
The kitchen's too big.

1545
02:25:22.380 --> 02:25:24.507
Sylvie. I need to speak to your father.

1546
02:25:27.302 --> 02:25:28.803
Is Louis there?

1547
02:25:30.472 --> 02:25:33.225
I need to speak to your father.
Have him call me.

1548
02:25:33.308 --> 02:25:37.145
212-664-7665.

1549
02:25:37.812 --> 02:25:40.315
I'll wait. He must call me. I'll wait.

1550
02:25:44.486 --> 02:25:46.029
Am I being hunted?

1551
02:25:46.696 --> 02:25:48.323
Is my family being hunted?

1552
02:25:48.448 --> 02:25:53.370
How is your father?
He's well? Your family is well?

1553
02:25:53.495 --> 02:25:57.082
I don't know. How is my family?
Are they well?

1554
02:25:57.165 --> 02:25:58.500
Are they going to be okay?

1555
02:25:58.625 --> 02:26:01.336
I'm sending you a parcel
of sausage and cheese.

1556
02:26:01.461 --> 02:26:04.506
Real cheese.
The kind you can't find in America.

1557
02:26:04.673 --> 02:26:08.176
It isn't pasteurised.
so it won't taste like shit.

1558
02:26:09.511 --> 02:26:12.514
It's a real pleasure
to hear your voice again.

1559
02:26:13.682 --> 02:26:15.892
I think about you with concern.

1560
02:26:16.351 --> 02:26:18.019
Do you believe me?

1561
02:26:20.021 --> 02:26:21.064
Avner?

1562
02:26:21.856 --> 02:26:23.733
You believe me. Avner?

1563
02:26:25.986 --> 02:26:27.612
You know my name?

1564
02:26:27.696 --> 02:26:29.197
Of course I do.

1565
02:26:30.865 --> 02:26:33.034
Now. listen to me. It's important.

1566
02:26:34.202 --> 02:26:37.080
No harm will come to you from me.

1567
02:27:02.063 --> 02:27:05.608
You can't go in there. sir.
It's a restricted area. Sir?

1568
02:27:06.359 --> 02:27:08.445
I tried to stop him.
I don't know who this guy is.

1569
02:27:08.570 --> 02:27:11.072
Security!

1570
02:27:12.407 --> 02:27:14.034
If you're Mossad. you know who I am.

1571
02:27:14.117 --> 02:27:16.995
If you don't. tell Ephraim
Avner came to see him.

1572
02:27:17.078 --> 02:27:18.496
Being in this room
is by appointment only.

1573
02:27:18.580 --> 02:27:20.081
Shut up and listen to me.

1574
02:27:20.206 --> 02:27:22.709
I won't hesitate to kill
other people's children

1575
02:27:22.792 --> 02:27:24.794
- if you hurt my child. Understand?
- Do I know you. sir?

1576
02:27:24.919 --> 02:27:27.964
Or wives if you hurt my wife.
or fathers if you hurt my father.

1577
02:27:28.089 --> 02:27:30.258
I don't care. I'll go to the newspapers.

1578
02:27:30.383 --> 02:27:33.219
I'll give every name of everybody
who was in the meetings.

1579
02:27:33.303 --> 02:27:37.098
I'll tell them everything if you
don't leave my family alone! Okay?

1580
02:32:05.908 --> 02:32:07.243
I love you.

1581
02:32:32.268 --> 02:32:33.436
Avner.

1582
02:32:39.067 --> 02:32:40.568
Phone for you.

1583
02:32:41.069 --> 02:32:42.570
He's Israeli.

1584
02:32:47.450 --> 02:32:49.786
You think we'd hurt your family?

1585
02:32:50.244 --> 02:32:52.872
I think anyone is capable of anything.

1586
02:32:53.247 --> 02:32:55.583
I think you're losing your mind.

1587
02:33:00.588 --> 02:33:02.298
Did I commit murder?

1588
02:33:05.551 --> 02:33:07.637
I want you to give me proof that
everyone we killed

1589
02:33:07.762 --> 02:33:08.805
had a hand in Munich.

1590
02:33:08.930 --> 02:33:11.140
I don't discuss such things
with people who don't exist.

1591
02:33:11.265 --> 02:33:13.768
You want to discuss.
come back to existence.

1592
02:33:13.893 --> 02:33:15.853
You want your daughter
to grow up in exile?

1593
02:33:15.937 --> 02:33:17.563
I want evidence.

1594
02:33:21.275 --> 02:33:24.612
Professor Hamshari
with the beautiful wife and child?

1595
02:33:24.946 --> 02:33:28.241
He was implicated in a failed
assassination attempt on Ben-Gurion.

1596
02:33:28.324 --> 02:33:30.660
He was recruiting for Fatah France.

1597
02:33:30.785 --> 02:33:31.994
You stopped him.

1598
02:33:32.120 --> 02:33:33.621
We should have tried
to bring him to Israel.

1599
02:33:33.746 --> 02:33:35.748
And Zwaiter. your harmless
little writer in Rome?

1600
02:33:35.832 --> 02:33:39.043
He was behind the bomb
on El Al flight 76 in 1968.

1601
02:33:39.127 --> 02:33:40.962
He was working on another bomb
last August.

1602
02:33:41.087 --> 02:33:42.130
I could go on and on with this.

1603
02:33:42.255 --> 02:33:44.757
According to evidence nobody has seen.

1604
02:33:44.841 --> 02:33:47.635
If these people committed crimes.
we should have arrested them.

1605
02:33:47.760 --> 02:33:49.262
Like Eichmann.

1606
02:33:49.762 --> 02:33:51.597
If these guys live. Israelis die.

1607
02:33:51.681 --> 02:33:55.643
Whatever doubts you have. Avner.
you know this is true.

1608
02:34:05.278 --> 02:34:07.488
You did well. but you're unhappy.

1609
02:34:07.613 --> 02:34:09.991
- I killed seven men.
- Not Salameh.

1610
02:34:10.825 --> 02:34:12.535
We'll get him. of course.

1611
02:34:15.496 --> 02:34:17.665
You think you were the only team?

1612
02:34:18.166 --> 02:34:21.002
It's a big operation.
You were only a part.

1613
02:34:21.210 --> 02:34:23.171
Does that assuage your guilt?

1614
02:34:24.297 --> 02:34:26.466
Did we accomplish anything at all?

1615
02:34:26.549 --> 02:34:29.343
Every man we killed
has been replaced by worse.

1616
02:34:29.469 --> 02:34:32.180
Why cut my fingernails?
They'll grow back.

1617
02:34:32.513 --> 02:34:34.932
Did we Kill to replace
the terrorist leadership

1618
02:34:35.016 --> 02:34:36.350
or the Palestinian leadership?

1619
02:34:36.476 --> 02:34:38.144
You tell me what we've done.

1620
02:34:38.227 --> 02:34:39.937
You killed them for the sake of a country

1621
02:34:40.021 --> 02:34:41.856
you now choose to abandon.

1622
02:34:42.732 --> 02:34:46.652
The country your mother and father
built. that you were born into.

1623
02:34:46.736 --> 02:34:49.864
You killed them for Munich.
for the future. for peace.

1624
02:34:51.240 --> 02:34:54.368
There's no peace at the end of this.
no matter what you believe.

1625
02:34:54.494 --> 02:34:57.705
- You know this is true.
- Here's what I know.

1626
02:34:57.872 --> 02:34:59.874
Your father is sick.
your mother will be alone.

1627
02:34:59.999 --> 02:35:03.169
You're a sabra.
Your wife and daughter are sabras.

1628
02:35:04.045 --> 02:35:06.255
What I came to say is this.

1629
02:35:07.507 --> 02:35:08.841
come home.

1630
02:35:23.105 --> 02:35:25.399
Come to my house for dinner tonight.

1631
02:35:26.901 --> 02:35:28.945
Come on. You're a Jew.
you're a stranger.

1632
02:35:29.070 --> 02:35:31.656
It's written someplace or other
that I'm meant to

1633
02:35:31.739 --> 02:35:34.450
ask you to come
and break bread with me.

1634
02:35:35.034 --> 02:35:39.580
So break bread with me. Ephraim.

1635
02:35:43.584 --> 02:35:44.627
No.
